2012-04-05: Barry Smith
The official OBI definition, explaining the meaning of a class or property: 'Shall be Aristotelian, formalized and normalized. Can be augmented with colloquial definitions' is terrible.
Can you fix to something like:
A statement of necessary and sufficient conditions explaining the meaning of an expression referring to a class or property.
Alan Ruttenberg
Your proposed definition is a reasonable candidate, except that it is very common that necessary and sufficient conditions are not given. Mostly they are necessary, occasionally they are necessary and sufficient or just sufficient. Often they use terms that are not themselves defined and so they effectively can't be evaluated by those criteria.
On the specifics of the proposed definition:
We don't have definitions of 'meaning' or 'expression' or 'property'. For 'reference' in the intended sense I think we use the term 'denotation'. For 'expression', I think we you mean symbol, or identifier. For 'meaning' it differs for class and property. For class we want documentation that let's the intended reader determine whether an entity is instance of the class, or not. For property we want documentation that let's the intended reader determine, given a pair of potential relata, whether the assertion that the relation holds is true. The 'intended reader' part suggests that we also specify who, we expect, would be able to understand the definition, and also generalizes over human and computer reader to include textual and logical definition.
Personally, I am more comfortable weakening definition to documentation, with instructions as to what is desirable.
We also have the outstanding issue of how to aim different definitions to different audiences. A clinical audience reading chebi wants a different sort of definition documentation/definition from a chemistry trained audience, and similarly there is a need for a definition that is adequate for an ontologist to work with.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: peptide
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Amide derived from two or more amino carboxylic acid molecules (the same or different) by formation of a covalent bond from the carbonyl carbon of one to the nitrogen atom of another with formal loss of water. The term is usually applied to structures formed from α-amino acids, but it includes those derived from any amino carboxylic acid. X = OH, OR, NH2, NHR, etc.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: deoxyribonucleic acid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: High molecular weight, linear polymers, composed of nucleotides containing deoxyribose and linked by phosphodiester bonds; DNA contain the genetic information of organisms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glucose
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An aldohexose used as a source of energy and metabolic intermediate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: lipid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: 'Lipids' is a loosely defined term for substances of biological origin that are soluble in nonpolar solvents. They consist of saponifiable lipids, such as glycerides (fats and oils) and phospholipids, as well as nonsaponifiable lipids, principally steroids.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hexose
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any six-carbon monosaccharide which in its linear form contains either an aldehyde group at position 1 (aldohexose) or a ketone group at position 2 (ketohexose).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecular entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: fat-soluble vitamin (role)
fat-soluble vitamin (role)
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any vitamin that dissolves in fats and are stored in body tissues. Unlike the water-soluble vitamins, they are stored in the body for long periods of time and generally pose a greater risk for toxicity when consumed in excess.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A chemical entity is a physical entity of interest in chemistry including molecular entities, parts thereof, and chemical substances.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: biological role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a biological context.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organic heterocyclic compound
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A cyclic compound having as ring members atoms of carbon and at least of one other element.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hydroxides
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Hydroxides are chemical compounds containing a hydroxy group or salts containing hydroxide (OH<small><sup>−</small></sup>).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: oxoacid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A compound which contains oxygen, at least one other element, and at least one hydrogen bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any polyatomic entity that is an electrically neutral entity consisting of more than one atom.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: monocarboxylic acid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An oxoacid containing a single carboxy group.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: monounsaturated fatty acid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any fatty acid with one double or triple bond in the fatty acid chain and singly bonded carbon atoms in the rest of the chain. MUFAs have positive effects on the cardiovascular system, and in diabetes treatment.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: polyunsaturated fatty acid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any fatty acid containing more than one double bond. Acids in this group are reported to have cardioprotective effects; and levels are lowered in chronic fatigue syndrome.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: saturated fatty acid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any fatty acid containing no carbon to carbon multiple bonds. Known to produce adverse biological effects when ingested to excess.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: unsaturated fatty acid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any fatty acid containing at least one C=C or C≡C bond.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: water-soluble vitamin (role)
water-soluble vitamin (role)
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any vitamin that dissolves in water and readily absorbed into tissues for immediate use. Unlike the fat-soluble vitamins, they are not stored in the body and need to be replenished regularly in the diet and will rarely accumulate to toxic levels since they are quickly excreted from the body via urine.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: amide
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An amide is a derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l ≠ 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: vitamin (role)
vitamin (role)
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A biochemical role played by any micronutrient that is an organic compound. Vitamins are present in foods in small amounts and are essential to normal metabolism and biochemical functions, usually as coenzymes. The term "vitamines" (from vita + amines) was coined in 1912 by Casimir Funk, who believed that these compounds were amines.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: atom
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A chemical entity constituting the smallest component of an element having the chemical properties of the element.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: primary amide
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l ≠ 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: heteroorganic entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A heteroorganic entity is an organic molecular entity in which carbon atoms or organic groups are bonded directly to one or more heteroatoms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pnictogen molecular entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A p-block molecular entity containing any pnictogen.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: chalcogen molecular entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any p-block molecular entity containing a chalcogen.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carboxylic acid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A carbon oxoacid acid carrying at least one ‒C(=O)OH group and having the structure RC(=O)OH, where R is any any monovalent functional group. Carboxylic acids are the most common type of organic acid.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: main group molecular entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms from any of groups 1, 2, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, and 18 of the periodic table.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cyclic compound
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any molecule that consists of a series of atoms joined together to form a ring.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: aromatic compound
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A cyclically conjugated molecular entity with a stability (due to delocalization) significantly greater than that of a hypothetical localized structure (e.g. Kekulé structure) is said to possess aromatic character.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: s-block molecular entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An s-block molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an s-block element.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: p-block molecular entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A main group molecular entity that contains one or more atoms of a p-block element.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: biomacromolecule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A macromolecule formed by a living organism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleic acid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A macromolecule made up of nucleotide units and hydrolysable into certain pyrimidine or purine bases (usually adenine, cytosine, guanine, thymine, uracil), <small>D</small>-ribose or 2-deoxy-<small>D</small>-ribose and phosphoric acid.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ribonucleic acid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: High molecular weight, linear polymers, composed of nucleotides containing ribose and linked by phosphodiester bonds; RNA is central to the synthesis of proteins.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organic cyclic compound
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any organic molecule that consists of atoms connected in the form of a ring.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: heteroarene
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A heterocyclic compound formally derived from an arene by replacement of one or more methine (‒C=) and/or vinylene (‒CH=CH‒) groups by trivalent or divalent heteroatoms, respectively, in such a way as to maintain the continuous π-electron system characteristic of aromatic systems and a number of out-of-plane π-electrons corresponding to the Hückel rule (4n+2).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: macromolecule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A macromolecule is a molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: aldohexose
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A hexose with a (potential) aldehyde group at one end.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organonitrogen compound
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any heteroorganic entity containing at least one carbon-nitrogen bond.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: fatty acid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any aliphatic monocarboxylic acid derived from or contained in esterified form in an animal or vegetable fat, oil or wax. Natural fatty acids commonly have a chain of 4 to 28 carbons (usually unbranched and even-numbered), which may be saturated or unsaturated. By extension, the term is sometimes used to embrace all acyclic aliphatic carboxylic acids.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: monosaccharide
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Parent monosaccharides are polyhydroxy aldehydes H[CH(OH)]nC(=O)H or polyhydroxy ketones H‒[CHOH]n‒C(=O)[CHOH]m‒H with three or more carbon atoms. The generic term 'monosaccharide' (as opposed to oligosaccharide or polysaccharide) denotes a single unit, without glycosidic connection to other such units. It includes aldoses, dialdoses, aldoketoses, ketoses and diketoses, as well as deoxy sugars, provided that the parent compound has a (potential) carbonyl group.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: protein
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A biological macromolecule minimally consisting of one polypeptide chain synthesized at the ribosome.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: polyatomic entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any molecular entity consisting of more than one atom.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbonyl compound
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any compound containing the carbonyl group, C=O. The term is commonly used in the restricted sense of aldehydes and ketones, although it actually includes carboxylic acids and derivatives.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organic oxo compound
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Organic compounds containing an oxygen atom, =O, doubly bonded to carbon or another element.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organochalcogen compound
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organochalcogen compound is a compound containing at least one carbon-chalcogen bond.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organooxygen compound
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organochalcogen compound containing at least one carbon-oxygen bond.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: heteroatomic molecular entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A molecular entity consisting of two or more chemical elements.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carboxamide
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An amide of a carboxylic acid, having the structure RC(=O)NR<small><sub>2</sub></small>. The term is used as a suffix in systematic name formation to denote the ‒C(=O)NH<small><sub>2</sub></small> group including its carbon atom.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organic amino compound
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A compound formally derived from ammonia by replacing one, two or three hydrogen atoms by organyl groups.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organic molecular entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any molecular entity that contains carbon.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role is particular behaviour which a material entity may exhibit.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: physiological role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A biological role relating to the normal mechanisms and their interactions within a living system.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: heterocyclic compound
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A cyclic compound having as ring members atoms of at least two different elements.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleobase-containing molecular entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any compound that has a nucleobase as a part.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organic acid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any organic molecular entity that is acidic and contains carbon in covalent linkage.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organic molecule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any molecule that consists of at least one carbon atom as part of the electrically neutral entity.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food component
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A physiological role played by any substance that is distributed in foodstuffs. It includes materials derived from plants or animals, such as vitamins or minerals, as well as environmental contaminants.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbohydrates and carbohydrate derivatives
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any organooxygen compound that is a polyhydroxy-aldehyde or -ketone, or a compound derived from one. Carbohydrates contain only carbon, hydrogen and oxygen and usually have an empirical formula Cm(H2O)n; carbohydrate derivatives may contain other elements by substitution or condensation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cell
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material entity of anatomical origin (part of or deriving from an organism) that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cultured cell
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A cell in vitro that is or has been maintained or propagated as part of a cell culture.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: experimentally modified cell in vitro
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A cell in vitro that has undergone physical changes as a consequence of a deliberate and specific experimental procedure.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: clinical measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quantitative or qualitative value which is the result of an act of assessing a morphological or physiological state or property in a single individual or sample or a group of individuals or samples, based on direct observation or experimental manipulation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: whole body morphological measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Morphological measurement involving the entire body of an organism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: body weight
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The heaviness or degree to which an entire organism's body is drawn to the earth by gravity.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: body morphological measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Measurement of the structure or forms of the entire body or parts of the body of an organism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: calculated body morphological measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: This is a measurement of the physical form or structure of an organism which has been normalized, adjusted or derived by a mathematical process or computation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood chemistry measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quantification of a parameter of the chemical composition of blood.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood protein measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any measurement involving the amount, composition or type of protein, the complex organic compounds containing carbon, hydrogen, oxygen, nitrogen, and sulfur consisting of alpha-amino acids joined by peptide linkages, in blood.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A measurement of the blood, it's contents, cells or other factors contained within the blood.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood steroid level
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The level of steroids found in a specific volume of blood.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood lipid measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any value resulting from the quantification of a morphological or physiological parameter of a blood-derived lipid, any of a structurally diverse group of organic compounds found in blood that are insoluble in water but soluble innonpolar solvents that, among other biological functions, serve as a source of fuel and are an important constituent of cell structure.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood total cholesterol level
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Measurement of the entire amount of cholesterol, a eukaryotic sterol that in higher animals is the precursor of bile acids and steroid hormones and a key constituent of cell membranes, without taking into account any association with other molecules such as lipoproteins, in a specified volume of blood, the fluid that circulates through the heart, arteries, capillaries and veins carrying nutrients and oxygen to the body tissues and metabolites away from them.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood high density lipoprotein cholesterol level
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Measurement of the amount of cholesterol, a eukaryotic sterol that in higher animals is the precursor of bile acids and steroid hormones and a key constituent of cell membranes, carried in high-density lipoprotein (HDL) molecules in a specified volume of blood, the fluid that circulates through the heart, arteries, capillaries and veins carrying nutrients and oxygen to the body tissues and metabolites away from them. HDL is the smallest of the major lipoprotein particles, complex molecules that consist of a protein membrane surrounding a core of lipids. The HDL class of lipoproteins, specifically the subtypes of HDL2 and HDL3, have densities between 1.063 and 1.210 g/ml.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood low density lipoprotein cholesterol level
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Measurement of the amount of cholesterol, a eukaryotic sterol that in higher animals is the precursor of bile acids and steroid hormones and a key constituent of cell membranes, carried in low-density lipoprotein (LDL) molecules in a specified volume of blood, the fluid that circulates through the heart, arteries, capillaries and veins carrying nutrients and oxygen to the body tissues and metabolites away from them. LDL constitute a class of relatively large, heterogeneous lipoprotein particles, complex molecules that consist of a protein membrane surrounding a core of lipids. The LDL class of lipoproteins has a density between 1.019 and 1.063 g/ml. In some animal species, such as canine and rodents, this may overlap with the HDL1 class and be designated LDL/HDL1.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: body mass index (BMI)
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A measurement relating body weight to height in an organism; typically calculated as the weight of an individual divided by the height of that individual squared. For quadrupeds, the square of body height is often replaced by the square of body length.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood lipoprotein level
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The amount of lipoproteins, any of a group of conjugated proteins that have at least one lipid component, in a specific volume of blood.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: consumption measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The quantification of any morphological or physiological parameter related to intake or ingestion, especially of food or drink, or a value resulting from such a quantification.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: drink intake rate
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Amount of drink, that is, a liquid that is brought into the mouth and swallowed to quench thirst, for nourishment, etc., consumed per unit time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: drink intake measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The quantification of any parameter related to the process whereby drink, any liquid that is brought into the mouth and swallowed to quench thirst, for nourishment, etc., is taken in for utilization by the body.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food intake measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The quantification of any parameter related to the process whereby food (i.e. material, usually of plant or animal origin, that contains essential nutrients such as carbohydrates, fats, proteins, vitamins, and/or minerals and that is ingested and assimilated by an organism to produce energy, stimulate growth, and maintain life) is taken in for utilization by the body.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ethanol drink intake rate
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The amount of ethanol, a colorless volatile flammable liquid CH3CH2OH that is the intoxicating agent in liquors, consumed per unit time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood sterol level
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The amount of sterol, any of a group of steroids with a long (8 to 10 carbons) aliphatic side-chain at position 17 and at least one alcoholic group, in a specified sample of blood.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood cholesterol level
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The amount of cholesterol, a eukaryotic sterol that in higher animals is the precursor of bile acids and steroid hormones and a key constituent of cell membranes, in a specified sample of blood. Cholesterol in the blood is generally associated with various lipoproteins.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood lipoprotein measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A value resulting from the quantification of a morphological or physiological parameter of a blood-derived lipoprotein, any of a class of complex molecules found in blood that consist of a protein membrane surrounding a core of lipids.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood lipoprotein cholesterol level
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Measurement of the amount of cholesterol, a eukaryotic sterol that in higher animals is the precursor of bile acids and steroid hormones and a key constituent of cell membranes, carried in lipoprotein molecules in a specified volume of blood. Lipoprotein particles are complexes that consist of protein surrounding a core of lipids.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organism
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000116: 'Maximal functionally integrated unit' is intended to express unity, which Barry considers synonymous with BFO 'object'.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material entity that is a maximal functionally integrated unit that develops from a program encoded in a genome
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000116: Includes virus - we will later have a class for cellular organisms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: processed material entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material entity processed by human activity with an intent to produce it.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000116: In the COB 2024 workshop there was much disagreement about this label.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: planned process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A process that is initiated by an agent who intends to carry out a plan to achieve an objective through one or more actions as described in a plan specification.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material processing
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A completely executed planned process that intends to output material entities from input material entities

owl:Class.rdfs:label: device
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A processed material entity which is designed to be capable of a process.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: national geopolitical entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A political association with effective dominion over a geographic area.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: political entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A geographical region whose affairs and population are administered by an authority.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: astronomical body part
geophysical entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material part of an astronomical body.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Food material for humans and animals which is processed with the intention that it be consumable as a whole or added to other food products.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: mammalian meat food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A food product made of meat, the skeletal muscle and associated fat, and other edible tissues such as organs, livers, skin, brains, bone marrow, kidneys, or lungs, of mammals.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: plant food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A food product which has as a defining ingredient some plant material.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: animal seafood product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A seafood product is a vertebrate or invertibrate organism from an aquatic environment.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: vertebrate food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A food product which is derived from or produced by an animal that has a vertibrae.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: avian egg food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A food product made from an avian egg.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: swine food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Suidae is a family of artiodactyl mammals which are commonly called pigs, hogs or boars. In addition to numerous fossil species, 17 extant species are currently recognized (or 18 counting domestic pigs and wild boars separately), classified into between four and eight genera. The family includes the domestic pig, Sus scrofa domesticus or Sus domesticus, in addition to numerous species of wild pig, such as babirusas and warthogs. All suids, or swine, are native to the Old World, ranging from Asia to Europe and Africa.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: fungus food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A food product consisting of an edible fungi or mushroom or yeast.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: prepared food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Food product that is 1) ready or nearly ready for consumption; 2) usually a composite of several foods or ingredients that often belong to distinct product types; 3) usually formulated, mixed and partially or fully cooked.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: algae material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material which derives from algae (including single-celled microalgae and multicellular macroalgae).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: fish food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A fish food product includes products made from any fish species (aquatic vertebrate with gills and fins).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: avian food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A food product that is derived from some avian animal.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: dairy food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A dairy food product has mammilian milk or a milk component as an ingredient.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: milk or milk based food product
egg food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A food consisting of a round or oval body laid by the female of many animals, consisting of an ovum surrounded by layers of membranes and an outer casing, which acts to nourish and protect a developing embryo and its nutrient reserves.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: animal based refined or partially-refined food product
animal based salad food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A salad food product with one or more animal products (meat, milk, fat, eggs etc.) as ingredients.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: animal fat or oil refined food product
animal product based flavoring or seasoning
food material component
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Food material which normally exists as an ingredient to another food material, rather than eaten on its own. This includes chemical food components.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: salad food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A prepared food product consisting of either a salad or a salad ingredient mixture to which a salad dressing is added.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: soup food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A multi-component food product which is soup.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any substance that can be consumed by an organism to satisfy nutritional or other health needs, or to provide a social or organoleptic food experience

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food transformation process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A process involving the physical transformation of a food source or food product into some derived organic material or food product

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food material by characteristic
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Food material which has been categorized by a characteristic such as granularity or temperature.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: game animal food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Game or quarry is any animal hunted for sport or for food. The type and range of animals hunted for food varies in different parts of the world. In some countries, game is classified, including legal classification with respect to licences required, as either "small game" or "large game"

owl:Class.rdfs:label: multi-component food
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A food product consisting of food material derived from ingredients sourced from multiple organisms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food material by process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Food material organized by the process which it results from.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: lipid food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A lipid food product is a food product made primarily of plant or animal fat or oil

owl:Class.rdfs:label: animal
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A whole animal.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: vegetarian food material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A food product not including meat and animal tissue products (such as gelatin or animal-derived rennet).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food recipe
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A plan specification for making a food product, which may have ingredient, device, action and objective specifications.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: animal food product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A food product that is derived from some animal.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: plant material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Anatomical or other piece(s) or substance derived from one or more plants.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: fungus material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material which derives from one or more fungai.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: mammal material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material which derives from one or more mammals.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: vertebrate material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material which derives from one or more vertebrate animals.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: animal substance
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material which is produced by an animal.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: animal milk
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Milk which is produced by animal lactation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: animal milk (raw)
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Raw animal milk.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: avian material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material that derives from some avian animal.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: human milk (raw)
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Breast milk is the milk produced by the breasts (or mammary glands) of a human female.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: mammal
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Mammals (from Latin mamma "breast") are vertebrate animals constituting the class Mammalia, and characterized by the presence of mammary glands which in females produce milk for feeding (nursing) their young, a neocortex (a region of the brain), fur or hair, and three middle ear bones.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: vertebrate animal
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A vertebrate animal is any species of organism within the subphylum Vertebrata (chordates with backbones). Vertebrates represent the overwhelming majority of the phylum Chordata, with currently about 69,276 species described.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organism material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material which is distinguished primarily by the organism(s) it derives from.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: animal material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material that derives from one or more animals

owl:Class.rdfs:label: fat or oil
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Food substance or component consisting predominantly of mixed glycerol esters of fatty acids and, in far lesser amounts, of fatty acids, sterols and pigments. A fat is a solid at room temperature, an oil is a liquid at room temperature (20 degrees C.). Excludes essential oils.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: extract, concentrate or isolate of plant or animal
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A physical-chemical component separated from the food source or its parts by extraction, centrifugation, filtration, heat processing, expressing or a similar process. The separated component may be converted through further processing. If this is done, the final substance is indexed. A water-extracted component may remain in aqueous dispersion. The extract, concentrate or isolate is indexed in preference to the anatomic part from which it is derived. For example, peanut oil is indexed under *PEANUT* combined wih *FAT OR OIL* rather than with *SEED OR KERNEL*. On the other hand, fruit and vegetable juices can be indexed under *FRUIT JUICE OR NECTAR* or *VEGETABLE JUICE* (A. PRODUCT TYPE); therefore the anatomic part of the plant should be indexed.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food (liquid)
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A state of matter between a solid and a gas, in which a substance has the capacity to flow and conforms to the shape of the container.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food treatment process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Used to specifically characterize a food product based on the treatment or processes applied to the product or any indexed ingredient. The processes include adding, substituting or removing components or modifying the food or component, e.g., through fermentation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food preservation process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The methods contributing to the prevention or retardation of microbial, enzymatic or oxidative spoilage and thus to the extension of shelf life. Index all methods for which information is available, even if a corresponding descriptor has already been used in *H. TREATMENT APPLIED*. Preservation descriptors refer to the finished food as a whole with these exceptions: (1) if the components of a multi-component food, such as cream pie, are preservation by different methods, index all methods; (2) if chemical preservatives are declared on the label, always index them even if it is known that the preservative was introduced through or is only present in a component or ingredient of the food; and (3) if the preservation method for an ingredient is declared on the label (such as brie cheese made from pasteurized milk) index it. Also use *INGREDIENT preservation by THERMAL PROCESSING* or *INGREDIENT preservation by IRRADIATION* when ingredients have been pasteurized, ultrapasteurized, sterilized or irradiated.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete reproduction
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The production of new individuals that contain some portion of genetic material inherited from one or more parent organisms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: system process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in an organ system. An organ system is a regularly interacting or interdependent group of organs or tissues that work together to carry out a biological objective.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecular_function
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A molecular process that can be carried out by the action of a single macromolecular machine, usually via direct physical interactions with other molecular entities. Function in this sense denotes an action, or activity, that a gene product (or a complex) performs.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: catalytic activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of a biochemical reaction at physiological temperatures. In biologically catalyzed reactions, the reactants are known as substrates, and the catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein, but RNA that has catalytic activity (ribozyme) is often also regarded as enzymatic.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: 6-phosphofructokinase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + D-fructose-6-phosphate = ADP + D-fructose 1,6-bisphosphate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: fructose-bisphosphate aldolase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the reaction: beta-D-fructose 1,6-bisphosphate = D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + dihydroxyacetone phosphate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glucose-6-phosphate isomerase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the reaction: alpha-D-glucose 6-phosphate = beta-D-fructose 6-phosphate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate dehydrogenase (NAD+) (phosphorylating) activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the reaction: D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + phosphate + NAD+ = 3-phospho-D-glyceroyl phosphate + NADH + H+.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: lactate dehydrogenase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the reaction: lactate + NAD+ = H+ + NADH + pyruvate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hydrolase activity, hydrolyzing O-glycosyl compounds
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any O-glycosyl bond.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: beta-galactosidase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing beta-D-galactose residues in beta-D-galactosides.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phosphoglycerate kinase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the reaction: 3-phospho-D-glycerate + ATP = 3-phospho-D-glyceroyl phosphate + ADP + H+.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phosphoglycerate mutase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the reaction: (2R)-2-phosphoglycerate = (2R)-3-phosphoglycerate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phosphopyruvate hydratase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-phospho-D-glycerate = phosphoenolpyruvate + H2O.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: triose-phosphate isomerase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the reaction: D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate = dihydroxyacetone phosphate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbohydrate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: monosaccharide metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving monosaccharides, the simplest carbohydrates. They are polyhydric alcohols containing either an aldehyde or a keto group and between three to ten or more carbon atoms. They form the constitutional repeating units of oligo- and polysaccharides.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glucose metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving glucose, the aldohexose gluco-hexose. D-glucose is dextrorotatory and is sometimes known as dextrose; it is an important source of energy for living organisms and is found free as well as combined in homo- and hetero-oligosaccharides and polysaccharides.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glucose catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glucose, the aldohexose gluco-hexose.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organic acid metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving organic acids, any acidic compound containing carbon in covalent linkage.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: lactate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving lactate, the anion of lactic acid.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pyruvate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving pyruvate, 2-oxopropanoate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: generation of precursor metabolites and energy
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of precursor metabolites, substances from which energy is derived, and any process involved in the liberation of energy from these substances.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glycolytic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a carbohydrate into pyruvate, with the concomitant production of a small amount of ATP and the reduction of NAD(P) to NAD(P)H. Glycolysis begins with the metabolism of a carbohydrate to generate products that can enter the pathway and ends with the production of pyruvate. Pyruvate may be converted to acetyl-coenzyme A, ethanol, lactate, or other small molecules.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: fermentation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The metabolic process that uses oxidation-reduction reactions of organic compounds and substrate-level phosphorylation for the generation of adenosine triphosphate (ATP), without consuming oxygen and is independent of electron transport chains.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleobase-containing compound metabolic process
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: nucleobase, nucleoside, nucleotide and nucleic acid metabolism
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any cellular metabolic process involving nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: cellular nucleobase, nucleoside, nucleotide and nucleic acid metabolism
cellular nucleobase, nucleoside, nucleotide and nucleic acid metabolic process

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine nucleotide metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a purine nucleotide, a compound consisting of nucleoside (a purine base linked to a deoxyribose or ribose sugar) esterified with a phosphate group at either the 3' or 5'-hydroxyl group of the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete nucleoside diphosphate phosphorylation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The process of introducing a phosphate group into a nucleoside diphosphate to produce a nucleoside triphosphate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine nucleotide catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a purine nucleotide, a compound consisting of nucleoside (a purine base linked to a deoxyribose or ribose sugar) esterified with a phosphate group at either the 3' or 5'-hydroxyl group of the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete cellular aromatic compound metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving aromatic compounds, any organic compound characterized by one or more planar rings, each of which contains conjugated double bonds and delocalized pi electrons, as carried out by individual cells.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete NADH metabolic process
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: reduced nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving reduced nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NADH), a coenzyme present in most living cells and derived from the B vitamin nicotinic acid.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: NADH regeneration
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A metabolic process that generates a pool of NADH by the reduction of NAD+.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleoside phosphate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving any phosphorylated nucleoside.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete ATP generation from ADP
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The process of introducing a phosphate group into ADP, adenosine diphosphate, to produce ATP.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phosphorus metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the nonmetallic element phosphorus or compounds that contain phosphorus.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phosphate-containing compound metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the phosphate group, the anion or salt of any phosphoric acid.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete nitrogen compound metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving organic or inorganic compounds that contain nitrogen.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: digestion
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The whole of the physical, chemical, and biochemical processes carried out by multicellular organisms to break down ingested nutrients into components that may be easily absorbed and directed into metabolism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: behavior
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The internally coordinated responses (actions or inactions) of animals (individuals or groups) to internal or external stimuli, via a mechanism that involves nervous system activity.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: feeding behavior
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Behavior associated with the intake of food.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: biological process
biological_process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A biological process is the execution of a genetically-encoded biological module or program. It consists of all the steps required to achieve the specific biological objective of the module. A biological process is accomplished by a particular set of molecular functions carried out by specific gene products (or macromolecular complexes), often in a highly regulated manner and in a particular temporal sequence.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A cellular process consisting of the biochemical pathways by which a living organism transforms chemical substances. This includes including anabolism (biosynthetic process) and catabolism (catabolic process). Metabolic processes includes the transformation of small molecules, as well macromolecular processes such as DNA repair and replication, protein synthesis and degradation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phosphofructokinase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a phosphofructose substrate molecule.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A cellular process consisting of the biochemical pathways by which a living organism breaks down substances. This includes the breakdown of carbon compounds with the liberation of energy for use by the cell or organism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: biosynthetic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A cellular process consisting of the biochemical pathways by which a living organism synthesizes chemical substances. This typically represents the energy-requiring part of metabolism in which simpler substances are transformed into more complex ones.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleotide metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a nucleotide, a nucleoside that is esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the glycose moiety; may be mono-, di- or triphosphate; this definition includes cyclic nucleotides (nucleoside cyclic phosphates).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleoside diphosphate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a nucleoside diphosphate, a compound consisting of a nucleobase linked to a deoxyribose or ribose sugar esterified with diphosphate on the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleoside diphosphate catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a nucleoside diphosphate, a compound consisting of a nucleobase linked to a deoxyribose or ribose sugar esterified with diphosphate on the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine nucleoside diphosphate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving purine nucleoside diphosphate, a compound consisting of a purine base linked to a ribose or deoxyribose sugar esterified with diphosphate on the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine nucleoside diphosphate catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of purine nucleoside diphosphate, a compound consisting of a purine base linked to a ribose or deoxyribose sugar esterified with diphosphate on the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleoside triphosphate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a nucleoside triphosphate, a compound consisting of a nucleobase linked to a deoxyribose or ribose sugar esterified with triphosphate on the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine nucleoside triphosphate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving purine nucleoside triphosphate, a compound consisting of a purine base linked to a ribose or deoxyribose sugar esterified with triphosphate on the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine ribonucleotide metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a purine ribonucleotide, a compound consisting of ribonucleoside (a purine base linked to a ribose sugar) esterified with a phosphate group at either the 3' or 5'-hydroxyl group of the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine ribonucleotide catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a purine ribonucleotide, a compound consisting of ribonucleoside (a purine base linked to a ribose sugar) esterified with a phosphate group at either the 3' or 5'-hydroxyl group of the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleotide catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of nucleotides, any nucleoside that is esterified with (ortho)phosphate or an oligophosphate at any hydroxyl group on the glycose moiety; may be mono-, di- or triphosphate; this definition includes cyclic-nucleotides (nucleoside cyclic phosphates).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine ribonucleoside diphosphate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving purine ribonucleoside diphosphate, a compound consisting of a purine base linked to a ribose sugar esterified with diphosphate on the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine ribonucleoside diphosphate catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of purine ribonucleoside diphosphate, a compound consisting of a purine base linked to a ribose sugar esterified with diphosphate on the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ribonucleoside diphosphate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a ribonucleoside diphosphate, a compound consisting of a nucleobase linked to a ribose sugar esterified with diphosphate on the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ribonucleoside diphosphate catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a ribonucleoside diphosphate, a compound consisting of a nucleobase linked to a ribose sugar esterified with diphosphate on the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine ribonucleoside triphosphate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving purine ribonucleoside triphosphate, a compound consisting of a purine base linked to a ribose sugar esterified with triphosphate on the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ribonucleotide metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a ribonucleotide, a compound consisting of ribonucleoside (a base linked to a ribose sugar) esterified with a phosphate group at either the 3' or 5'-hydroxyl group of the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ribonucleotide catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a ribonucleotide, a compound consisting of ribonucleoside (a base linked to a ribose sugar) esterified with a phosphate group at either the 3' or 5'-hydroxyl group of the sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cellular process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any process that is carried out at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: galactosidase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of galactosyl compounds, substances containing a group derived from a cyclic form of galactose or a galactose derivative.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: energy derivation by oxidation of organic compounds
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways by which a cell derives energy from organic compounds; results in the oxidation of the compounds from which energy is released.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbohydrate catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organic acid biosynthetic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of organic acids, any acidic compound containing carbon in covalent linkage.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organic acid catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of organic acids, any acidic compound containing carbon in covalent linkage.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: kinase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phosphorylation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The process of introducing a phosphate group into a molecule, usually with the formation of a phosphoric ester, a phosphoric anhydride or a phosphoric amide.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: oxidoreductase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction, a reversible chemical reaction in which the oxidation state of an atom or atoms within a molecule is altered. One substrate acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and becomes oxidized, while the other acts as hydrogen or electron acceptor and becomes reduced.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH-OH group of donors
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-OH group act as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors, NAD or NADP as acceptor
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which an aldehyde or ketone (oxo) group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces NAD or NADP.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: transferase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor). Transferase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 2.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: transferase activity, transferring phosphorus-containing groups
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phosphotransferase activity, alcohol group as acceptor
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to an alcohol group (acceptor).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phosphotransferase activity, carboxyl group as acceptor
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to a carboxyl group (acceptor).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hydrolase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of various bonds, e.g. C-O, C-N, C-C, phosphoric anhydride bonds, etc.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hydrolase activity, acting on glycosyl bonds
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of any glycosyl bond.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: lyase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the cleavage of C-C, C-O, C-N and other bonds by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, or conversely adding a group to a double bond. They differ from other enzymes in that two substrates are involved in one reaction direction, but only one in the other direction. When acting on the single substrate, a molecule is eliminated and this generates either a new double bond or a new ring.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbon-carbon lyase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the cleavage of C-C bonds by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, or conversely adding a group to a double bond.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: aldehyde-lyase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the cleavage of a C-C bond in a molecule containing a hydroxyl group and a carbonyl group to form two smaller molecules, each being an aldehyde or a ketone.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbon-oxygen lyase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the breakage of a carbon-oxygen bond.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hydro-lyase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the cleavage of a carbon-oxygen bond by elimination of water.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: isomerase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the geometric or structural changes within one molecule. Isomerase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 5.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: intramolecular oxidoreductase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which the hydrogen donor and acceptor are the same molecule, and no oxidized product appears.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: intramolecular oxidoreductase activity, interconverting aldoses and ketoses
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which the hydrogen donor and acceptor, which is an aldose or a ketose, are the same molecule, and no oxidized product appears.
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: intramolecular isomerase activity, interconverting aldoses and ketoses

owl:Class.rdfs:label: intramolecular transferase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the transfer of a functional group from one position to another within a single molecule.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: intramolecular phosphotransferase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group from one position to another within a single molecule.
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: phosphotransferase activity, with regeneration of donors, apparently catalyzing intramolecular transfers

owl:Class.rdfs:label: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which an aldehyde or ketone (oxo) group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbohydrate kinase activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a carbohydrate substrate molecule.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: lactate biosynthetic process from pyruvate
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of lactate from other compounds, including pyruvate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: lactate biosynthetic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of lactate, the anion of lactic acid.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hexose metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a hexose, any monosaccharide with a chain of six carbon atoms in the molecule.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hexose catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of hexose, any monosaccharide with a chain of six carbon atoms in the molecule.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pyridine nucleotide catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a pyridine nucleotide, a nucleotide characterized by a pyridine derivative as a nitrogen base.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organophosphate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving organophosphates, any phosphate-containing organic compound.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glucose catabolic process to lactate
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The anaerobic enzymatic chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glucose to lactate, and possibly ethanol, yielding energy in the form of adenosine triphosphate (ATP).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pyruvate fermentation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The fermentation process resulting in the oxygen-independent conversion of pyruvate to reduced end products (e.g., lactate, ethanol, and acetate), accompanied by the concomitant oxidation of NADH to NAD.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: homolactic fermentation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The anaerobic enzymatic chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glucose to lactate, via canonical glycolysis, yielding energy in the form of adenosine triphosphate (ATP).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: NAD+ metabolic process
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: oxidized nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NAD+), a coenzyme that interconverts with its reduced form, NADH, in many redox and catabolic reactions.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ribose phosphate metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving ribose phosphate, any phosphorylated ribose sugar.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carboxylic acid metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving carboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one or more carboxyl (COOH) groups or anions (COO-).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: digestive system process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A physical, chemical, or biochemical process carried out by living organisms to break down ingested nutrients into components that may be easily absorbed and directed into metabolism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hemopoiesis
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the myeloid and lymphoid derived organ/tissue systems of the blood and other parts of the body over time, from formation to the mature structure. The site of hemopoiesis is variable during development, but occurs primarily in bone marrow or kidney in many adult vertebrates.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: multicellular organismal process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any biological process, occurring at the level of a multicellular organism, pertinent to its function.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: developmental process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an integrated living unit: an anatomical structure (which may be a subcellular structure, cell, tissue, or organ), or organism over time from an initial condition to a later condition.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: monocarboxylic acid metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving monocarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (COOH) group or anion (COO-).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete cellular nitrogen compound metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving various organic and inorganic nitrogenous compounds, as carried out by individual cells.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleobase-containing compound catabolic process
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: nucleobase, nucleoside, nucleotide and nucleic acid degradation
nucleobase, nucleoside, nucleotide and nucleic acid catabolism
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: nucleobase, nucleoside, nucleotide and nucleic acid breakdown

owl:Class.rdfs:label: eating behavior
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The specific behavior of an organism relating to the intake of food, any substance (usually solid) that can be metabolized by an organism to give energy and build tissue.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: drinking behavior
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The specific behavior of an organism relating to the intake of liquids, especially water.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pyruvate catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of pyruvate, 2-oxopropanoate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: oxoacid metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving any oxoacid; an oxoacid is a compound which contains oxygen, at least one other element, and at least one hydrogen bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate dehydrogenase [NAD(P)+] (phosphorylating) activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Catalysis of the reaction: D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + phosphate + NAD(P)+ = 3-phospho-D-glyceroyl phosphate + NAD(P)H + H+.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete cellular metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: primary metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving those compounds which are formed as a part of the normal anabolic and catabolic processes. These processes take place in most, if not all, cells of the organism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete cellular biosynthetic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of substances, carried out by individual cells.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: small molecule metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving small molecules, any low molecular weight, monomeric, non-encoded molecule.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: small molecule catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of small molecules, any low molecular weight, monomeric, non-encoded molecule.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: small molecule biosynthetic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of small molecules, any low molecular weight, monomeric, non-encoded molecule.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ADP metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving ADP, adenosine 5'-diphosphate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ADP catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of ADP, adenosine 5'-diphosphate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ATP metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving ATP, adenosine triphosphate, a universally important coenzyme and enzyme regulator.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: monosaccharide catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of monosaccharides, polyhydric alcohols containing either an aldehyde or a keto group and between three to ten or more carbon atoms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carboxylic acid biosynthetic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of carboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one or more carboxyl (-COOH) groups.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carboxylic acid catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of carboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one or more carboxyl (-COOH) groups.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organophosphate catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of organophosphates, any phosphate-containing organic compound.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete heterocycle metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving heterocyclic compounds, those with a cyclic molecular structure and at least two different atoms in the ring (or rings).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nicotinamide nucleotide metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving nicotinamide nucleotides, any nucleotide that contains combined nicotinamide.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete nucleotide phosphorylation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The process of introducing one or more phosphate groups into a nucleotide to produce a phosphorylated nucleoside.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cell development
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The cellular developmental process in which a specific cell progresses from an immature to a mature state. Cell development start once cell commitment has taken place.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: anatomical structure development
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an anatomical structure from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the structure and ends with the mature structure, whatever form that may be including its natural destruction. An anatomical structure is any biological entity that occupies space and is distinguished from its surroundings. Anatomical structures can be macroscopic such as a carpel, or microscopic such as an acrosome.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cellular developmental process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cell over time from an initial condition to a later condition.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: intestinal absorption
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A process in which nutrients are taken up from the contents of the intestine.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleobase-containing small molecule metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The cellular chemical reactions and pathways involving a nucleobase-containing small molecule: a nucleobase, a nucleoside, or a nucleotide.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glycolytic process through fructose-6-phosphate
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a monosaccharide into pyruvate, occurring through a fructose-6-phosphate intermediate, with the concomitant production of ATP and NADH.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glycolytic process through glucose-6-phosphate
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a carbohydrate into pyruvate, occurring through a glucose-6-phosphate intermediate, with the concomitant production of a small amount of ATP.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: canonical glycolysis
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The glycolytic process that begins with the conversion of glucose to glucose-6-phosphate by glucokinase activity. Glycolytic processes are the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a carbohydrate into pyruvate, with the concomitant production of a small amount of ATP.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glucose catabolic process to pyruvate
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glucose, with the production of pyruvate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete organic substance metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving an organic substance, any molecular entity containing carbon.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: monocarboxylic acid catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of monocarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (-COOH) group.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: monocarboxylic acid biosynthetic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of monocarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (-COOH) group.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine-containing compound metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a purine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains purine or a formal derivative thereof.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine-containing compound catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a purine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains purine or a formal derivative thereof.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pyridine-containing compound metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a pyridine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains pyridine or a formal derivative thereof.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pyridine-containing compound catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a pyridine-containing compound, i.e. any compound that contains pyridine or a formal derivative thereof.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbohydrate derivative metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrate derivative.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: carbohydrate derivative catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of carbohydrate derivative.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleoside phosphate catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a nucleoside phosphate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete organic cyclic compound metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving organic cyclic compound.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete organonitrogen compound metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving organonitrogen compound.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete organic substance catabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of an organic substance, any molecular entity containing carbon.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete organic substance biosynthetic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of an organic substance, any molecular entity containing carbon.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete organic hydroxy compound metabolic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways involving organic hydroxy compound.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete organic hydroxy compound biosynthetic process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: OBSOLETE. The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of organic hydroxy compound.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Phenotypic abnormality
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A phenotypic abnormality.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Insulin resistance
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Increased resistance towards insulin, that is, diminished effectiveness of insulin in reducing blood glucose levels.
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Body fails to respond to insulin

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Malabsorption
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Impaired ability to absorb one or more nutrients from the intestine.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Abnormal intestine morphology
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An abnormality of the intestine. The closely related term enteropathy is used to refer to any disease of the intestine.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Abnormal circulating lipid concentration
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a lipid in the blood circulation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Lactose intolerance
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An inability to digest lactose.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Abnormal glucose homeostasis
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Abnormality of glucose homeostasis.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Abnormal homeostasis
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Abnormal gastrointestinal tract morphology
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Morphological abnormality of the GI tract
Abnormal shape of the digestive system
Morphological abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract
Morphological anomaly of the digestive system
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Abnormal structure of the gastrointestinal tract.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Abnormality of digestive system physiology
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A functional anomaly of the digestive system.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Abnormal digestive system morphology
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A structural anomaly of the digestive system.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Abnormal circulating metabolite concentration
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An abnormal level of an analyte measured in the blood.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Abnormal circulating organic compound concentration
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any deviation of the concentration of an orrganic compound from the normal range. An organic compound is defined as any compound that contains a carbon atom.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: conditional specification
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A directive information entity that specifies what should happen if the trigger condition is fulfilled.
a directive information entity that specifies what should happen if the trigger condition is fulfilled

owl:Class.rdfs:label: measurement unit label
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A measurement unit label is as a label that is part of a scalar measurement datum and denotes a unit of measure.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: objective specification
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When part of a plan specification the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: OBI Plan and Planned Process/Roles Branch

owl:Class.rdfs:label: action specification
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A directive information entity that describes an action the bearer will take.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: OBI Plan and Planned Process branch

owl:Class.rdfs:label: datum label
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A label is a symbol that is part of some other datum and is used to either partially define the denotation of that datum or to provide a means for identifying the datum as a member of the set of data with the same label

owl:Class.rdfs:label: journal article
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A report that is published in a journal.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: data item
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: symbol
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity that is a mark(s) or character(s) used as a conventional representation of another entity.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: information entity
information
information content entity
