owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A generically dependent continuant that is about some thing.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: scalar measurement datum
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A scalar measurement datum is a measurement datum that is composed of two parts, numerals and a unit label.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: directive information entity
directive information entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: graph
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A diagram that presents one or more tuples of information by mapping those tuples in to a two dimensional space in a non arbitrary way.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: rule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A rule is an executable which guides, defines, restricts actions.
a rule is an executable which guides, defines, restricts actions

owl:Class.rdfs:label: algorithm
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A plan specification which describes the inputs and output of mathematical functions as well as workflow of execution for achieving an predefined objective. Algorithms are realized usually by means of implementation as computer programs for execution by automata.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: adapted from discussion on OBI list (Matthew Pocock, Christian Cocos, Alan Ruttenberg)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: curation status specification
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The curation status of the term. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: report
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A document assembled by an author for the purpose of providing information for the audience. A report is the output of a documenting process and has the objective to be consumed by a specific audience. Topic of the report is on something that has completed. A report is not a single figure. Examples of reports are journal article, patent application, grant progress report, case report (not patient record).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: data set
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: data about an ontology part
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Data about an ontology part is a data item about a part of an ontology, for example a term

owl:Class.rdfs:label: plan specification
plan specification
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A directive information entity with action specifications and objective specifications as parts that, when concretized, is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives by taking the actions specified.

A directive information entity with action specifications and objective specifications as parts, and that may be concretized as a realizable entity that, if realized, is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives by taking the actions specified.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: OBI Plan and Planned Process branch

owl:Class.rdfs:label: measurement datum
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: version number
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A version number is an information content entity which is a sequence of characters borne by part of each of a class of manufactured products or its packaging and indicates its order within a set of other products having the same name.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: conclusion textual entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A textual entity that expresses the results of reasoning about a problem, for instance as typically found towards the end of scientific papers.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: textual entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A textual entity is a part of a manifestation (FRBR sense), a generically dependent continuant whose concretizations are patterns of glyphs intended to be interpreted as words, formulas, etc.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: citation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A textual entity intended to identify a particular publication.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: figure
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity consisting of a two dimensional arrangement of information content entities such that the arrangement itself is about something.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: diagram
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A figure that expresses one or more propositions

owl:Class.rdfs:label: document
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A collection of information content entities intended to be understood together as a whole

owl:Class.rdfs:label: publication
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A document that is the output of a publishing process.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: publication about an investigation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A publication that is about an investigation

owl:Class.rdfs:label: document part
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity that is part of a document.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: abstract
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A summary of the entire document that is substantially smaller than the document it summarizes. It is about the document it summarizes.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: methods section
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A part of a publication about an investigation that is about the study design of the investigation

owl:Class.rdfs:label: results section
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A part of a publication about an investigation that is about a study design execution

owl:Class.rdfs:label: discussion section of a publication about an investigation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A part of a publication about an investigation that is about the study interpretation of the investigation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: discussion section of a publication about an investigation

owl:Class.rdfs:label: supplementary material to a document
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A part of a document that is segregated from the rest of the document due to its size

owl:Class.rdfs:label: time measurement datum
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measuring a temporal interval

owl:Class.rdfs:label: author role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role inhering in a person or organization that is realized when the bearer participates in the work which is the basis of the document, in the writing of the document, and signs it with their name.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: data item extraction from journal article
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process in which journal articles are read or processed and data items are extracted, typically for further analysis or indexing

owl:Class.rdfs:label: documenting
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process in which a document is created or added to by including the specified input in it.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: assigning a centrally registered identifier
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process in which a new CRID is created, associated with an entity, and stored in the CRID registry thereby registering it as being associated with some entity

owl:Class.rdfs:label: centrally registered identifier symbol
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A symbol that is part of a CRID and that is sufficient to look up a record from the CRID's registry.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: Original proposal from Bjoern, discussions at IAO calls

owl:Class.rdfs:label: centrally registered identifier
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity that consists of a CRID symbol and additional information about the CRID registry to which it belongs.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: Original proposal from Bjoern, discussions at IAO calls

owl:Class.rdfs:label: centrally registered identifier registry
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A code set of CRID records, each consisting of a CRID symbol and additional information which was recorded in the code set through an assigning a centrally registered identifier process.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: Original proposal from Bjoern, discussions at IAO calls

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ethical approval section
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A part of a document about the governance body responsible for approving the work discussed in a document on an ethical basis.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ethical approval textual entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A textual entity that documents the ethical approval of some study design.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: statistical analysis section
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A part of the document used to describe the statistical methodologies employed in the work presented in the document.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: identifier
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity that is the outcome of a dubbing process and is used to refer to one instance of entity shared by a group of people to refer to that individual entity.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: personal name
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An identifier referring to an individual entity that is ascribed personhood by the user of the identifier.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: code set
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity that is a collection of other information content entities that has been created to identify or annotate things in a specified domain, and where the intention of its creators is that the collection has a one-to-one correspondence with those things.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: document act input document
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A document that is intended to be the specified input in a document act. It has a plan specification as a part that specifies the intended socio-legal entities that are created through the document (objective specification) and the way in which the document act is to be performed (by signing, by stamping, etc.) (action specification).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: informed consent form
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A document that explains all relevant information to assist a human being in understanding the expectations and requirements of participation in a process, and is an instrument in obtaining consent and, after having obtained consent, is a record that such a consent has occurred.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: signed informed consent form
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An informed consent form that has been signed by at least one participant.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: contact person for questions about research
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A person who is the contact for questions about research.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Subject Trial Set
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The collection of subjects that have a common set of parameters defined in the protocol (could be experimental parameters, treatment parameters, or sponsor-defined attributes).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: TMF-RM IRB or IEC Trial Approval Section
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The Trial Master File Reference Model section that contains a collection of documents related to the Institutional Review Board or Independent Ethics Committee decisions for the clinical trial.
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: TMF-RM IRB or IEC Trial Approval Section
Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Documents

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pyruvate
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of pyruvic acid, which is an important metabolic product for energy-producing biochemical pathways. Pyruvate is the final product of glycolysis and, when hypoxic conditions arise, can be metabolized anaerobically to form lactate. This chemical is a precursor of both acetyl-coenzyme A and oxaloacetate, which are involved in the citric acid cycle. Additionally, oxaloacetate is a substrate in the gluconeogenesis pathway.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Body Fat Percentage
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The amount of an individual's total body mass that is fat, expressed as a percent.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Follow-Up
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The process by which information about the health status of an individual is obtained after a study has officially closed; an activity that continues something that has already begun or that repeats something that has already been done.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Kefir
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A nutritional supplement composed of a fermented milk drink prepared by inoculating cow, goat, or sheep milk with kefir grains, with potential immunomodulating and probiotic activities. Upon oral administration of kefir, the kefir grains may stimulate the proliferation of beneficial bacteria in the gastrointestinal (GI) tract. This modulates the GI flora ecosystem, improves the functions of the intestinal barrier and protects against harmful viruses and bacteria. In addition, this prebiotic modulates the immune system and may inhibit inflammation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Research Center
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A facility established for research, often designed to promote interactions between faculty, scholars, students, and industry.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organic or inorganic substance, element, isotope, food or other materials derived from microorganism, plant, or animal sources. They can be used for the prevention, diagnosis, treatment or research of disease states, for industrial purposes, or for the promotion or maintenance of organism viability or health.
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Drug or Chemical by Structure
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Substances that are grouped or classified by chemical composition.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Food Component
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Substances introduced into the body by dietary means.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Personal Attribute
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The distinguishing qualities or prominent aspects of an individual person.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Organic Oxoacids
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Organic acids that have oxygen atoms in the acidic groups. (NCI)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Food or Food Product
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Processed or unprocessed substances obtained from animal, plant, microorganism and mining source that provide nutrients for living organisms to maintain biological processes or functions.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Study Related Group
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Groups with a focus on clinical or health related studies.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Conceptual Entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organizational header for concepts representing mostly abstract entities.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Identifier
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sampling
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The selection and obtaining of small representative quantities of biological, environmental, or other materials for the purpose of analysis.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Street Address
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The street name and building number where a person or organization is located.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Adherence
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The act of abiding by a stated treatment plan or protocol.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Control Group
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A group used as a standard of comparison in a control experiment.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Carbohydrate
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A class of hydrocarbons with an empirical formula of Cm(H20)n (where m and n may be equal) and includes monomers, polymers and derivatives of aldoses, ketoses, saccharides, and alditols.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Carboxylic Acids
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organic oxoacid that contains a carboxy moiety (-COOH) as a functional group.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Activity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An active process; excludes processes and mechanisms which fulfill biological functions.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Industrial Aid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Natural or synthetic substances that are used in various industries or in laboratories for a broad range of applications. This group includes, but is not limited to, pharmaceutical excipients, research/diagnostic agents, agricultural agents, and other non-edible products that may have human health implication.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Control Type
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A characteristic of a treatment regimen employed as a comparator against which the study treatment is evaluated.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Random Sampling
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A method of selecting a sample from a population in such a way that every sample that could be selected has an equal chance of being selected.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Simple Random Sampling
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A randomly chosen subset of individuals from a larger set.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Convenience Sampling
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Units are chosen for inclusion into a sample based on the convenience of accessibility of research.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Web Site
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A collection of web pages and other files.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Study Name
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The name applied to a scientific investigation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Stratified Random Sampling
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A statistical probability technique that divides a population into subgroups based on shared characteristics. A random sample is then drawn from each subgroup to ensure representation of all groups.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Judgment Sampling
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A statistical sampling technique where researchers use their knowledge and expertise to choose participants they believe are most representative and suitable for the study.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Multi-Stage Sampling
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A statistical sampling technique where samples are selected in multiple stages, with each subset of the population selected based on the previous stage's selection until the final sample is selected.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Organic Chemical
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Molecule that contains atoms of the element carbon, usually combined with itself and with atoms of one or more other element such as hydrogen, oxygen, nitrogen, sulfur, phosphorus, chlorine, or fluorine. Excludes carbides, carbonates and carbon oxides.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Drink
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A single serving of a beverage; any liquid suitable for drinking.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Probiotic
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Probiotic supplements (pills, liquid, powder; or other probiotics)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Study Objective Description
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The textual representation of the study objective.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Study Protocol Version Acronym
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The non-unique initials or abbreviated name used for identification of the study protocol document version.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Clinical Trial Registry Identifier
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A sequence of letters, numbers, or other characters that uniquely identifies a clinical trial within a clinical trial registry.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: data collection
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process that gathers and measures information on variables of interest, in an established systematic fashion that enables one to answer stated research questions, test hypotheses, and evaluate outcomes. Data collection results in a collection of data.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: randomization sampling design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A data sampling design that uses randomization for sample selection

owl:Class.rdfs:label: data matrix
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A data item that is more specifically a rectangular array of numbers, symbols, or expressions, arranged in rows and columns.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: data collection from literature
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A data collection process that results in a collection of data from the literature.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: transformed data item
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A data item that is produced as the output of a data transformation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: form filling
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A document editing process in which one or more fields in a form are filled with related information, such as when answering a questionnare.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: filled patient questionnaire
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A patient questionnaire which has been filled out by a patient.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: patient questionnaire
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A questionnaire that comprises a set of demographic and medical questions about a patient which will be filled by the patient or their legally authorized representative.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: smoking end date
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A time measurement datum which is the end date of a smoking behavior.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: standard operating procedure
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A protocol that is a set of step-by-step instructions compiled by an organization for carrying out routine operations.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sample collection or study aim description
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A textual entity describing a study aim or a sample collection.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: study proper name
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A proper name that designates a study.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: number of total human study participant objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An objective specification that specifies the total number of individuals who are planned to participate in study.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: obsolete planned process
planned process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A process that realizes a plan which is the concretization of a plan specification.
A processual entity that realizes a plan which is the concretization of a plan specification.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulator role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a regulatory role involved with making and/or enforcing relevant legislation and governmental orders

owl:Class.rdfs:label: biological feature identification objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Biological_feature_identification_objective is an objective role carried out by the proposition defining the aim of a study designed to examine or characterize a particular biological feature.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulatory role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a role which inheres in material entities and is realized in the processes of making, enforcing or being defined by legislation or orders issued by a governmental body.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material supplier role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a role realized through the process of supplying materials such as animal subjects, reagents or other materials used in an investigation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: processed material
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Is a material entity that is created or changed during material processing.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: chromatography device
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A device that facilitates the separation of mixtures. The function of a chromatography device involves passing a mixture dissolved in a "mobile phase" through a stationary phase, which separates the analyte to be measured from other molecules in the mixture and allows it to be isolated.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: mass spectrometer
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A mass spectrometer is an instrument which is used to measure the mass to charge ratio of ions. All mass spectrometers consist of three basic parts: an ion source, a mass analyzer, and a detector system. The stages within the mass spectrometer are: 1. Production of ions from the sample 2. Separation of ions with different masses 3. Detection of the number of ions of each mass produced 4.Collection of data to generate the mass spectrum

owl:Class.rdfs:label: investigation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a planned process that consists of parts: planning, study design execution, documentation and which produce conclusion(s).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: evaluant role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a role that inheres in a material entity that is realized in an assay in which data is generated about the bearer of the evaluant role

owl:Class.rdfs:label: assay
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process that has the objective to produce information about a material entity (the evaluant) by examining it.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sample preparation for assay
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A sample_preparation_for_assay is a protocol_application including material_enrollments and biomaterial_transformations. definition_source: OBI.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: diagnosis textual entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: diagnosis is an assessment of a disease or injury, its likely prognosis and treatment.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: culture medium
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a processed material that provides the needed nourishment for microorganisms or cells grown in vitro.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: reagent role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role inhering in a biological or chemical entity that is intended to be applied in a scientific technique to participate (or have molecular components that participate) in a chemical reaction that facilitates the generation of data about some entity distinct from the bearer, or the generation of some specified material output distinct from the bearer.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: patient role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a role which inheres in a person and is realized by the process of being under the care of a physician or health care provider

owl:Class.rdfs:label: protocol testing objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Protocol_testing_objective is a methodology_testing_objective role describing a study designed to examine the effects of using different protocols.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: participant under investigation role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role that is realized through the execution of a study design in which the bearer of the role participates and in which data about that bearer is collected.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: responsible party role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a study personnel role played by a party who is accountable for the execution of a study component and can make decisions about the conduct of the study

owl:Class.rdfs:label: principal investigator role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a responsible party role played by a person responsible for the overall conduct of a study

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role borne by a material entity that is obtained during a specimen collection process and that can be realized by performing measurements or observations on the specimen.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: intervention design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An intervention design is a study design in which a controlled process applied to the subjects (the intervention) serves as the independent variable manipulated by the experimentalist. The treatment (perturbation or intervention) defined can be defined as a combination of values taken by independent variable manipulated by the experimentalists are applied to the recruited subjects assigned (possibly by applying specific methods) to treatment groups. The specificity of intervention design is the fact that independent variables are being manipulated and a response of the biological system is evaluated via response variables as monitored by possibly a series of assays.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: baseline participant role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a reference participant role which is realized by making the reference to qualities at the start of the study or intervention

owl:Class.rdfs:label: filter paper
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A device manufacture with the intent to provide a porous unsized paper used for filtering.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: crossover population role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a role realized when a participant serves as reference to itself

owl:Class.rdfs:label: study group role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a study population role where the bearer is a population of material entities and the role is realized in the implementation of a study design wherein the entities bearing the study population role are observed or subjected to intervention according to the study design and are biological replicates, i.e. they receive the same treatment under the protocol

owl:Class.rdfs:label: population
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a population is a collection of individuals from the same taxonomic class living, counted or sampled at a particular site or in a particular area

owl:Class.rdfs:label: biological replicate role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a reference participant role realized by equivalent treatment of participants

owl:Class.rdfs:label: investigation agent role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role borne by an entity and that is realized in a process that is part of an investigation in which an objective is achieved. These processes include, among others: planning, overseeing, funding, reviewing.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: methodology testing objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Methodology_testing_objective is an objective role carried out by a proposition defining the aim of the study is to examine the effect of using different methodologies.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: reference subject role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a reference subject role which inheres in an organism or entity of organismal origin so that the characteristics or responses of the participant playing the reference participant role are used for comparison or reference

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organization
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An entity that can bear roles, has members, and has a set of organization rules. Members of organizations are either organizations themselves or individual people. Members can bear specific organization member roles that are determined in the organization rules. The organization rules also determine how decisions are made on behalf of the organization by the organization members.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: technical replicate role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: technical replicate role is realized when two portions from one evaluant are used in replicate runs of an assay

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cohort role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: WEB:http://www.sceoc.com/glossaryofterms/ # a group of individuals having a statistical factor (as age or class membership) in common in a demographic study, such as a cohort of students.
WEB:http://www.thebody.org/content/treat/art2612.html # a group of individuals in a study who share a demographic, clinical, or other statistical characteristic (eg, age, study site).

WEB:http://www.uhhospitals.org/tabid/591/Default.aspx # A cohort is a group of people with a common characteristic that is studied over a period of time as part of a scientific or medical investigation.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a cohort role is a biological replicate role played by a group of study participants who share a common characteristic of interest to the study.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: plan
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A plan is a realizable entity that is the inheres in a bearer who is committed to realizing it as a completely executed planned process.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: protocol
protocol
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A plan specification which has sufficient level of detail and quantitative information to communicate it between investigation agents, so that different investigation agents will reliably be able to independently reproduce the process.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: adding a material entity into a target
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: adding a material entity into a target
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: is a process with the objective to place a material entity bearing the 'material to be added role' into a material bearing the 'target of material addition role'.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: analyte role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A measurand role borne by a molecular entity or an atom and realized in an analyte assay which achieves the objective to measure the magnitude/concentration/amount of the analyte in the entity bearing evaluant role.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material to be added role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role of a material entity that is realized in an "adding a material entity into a target" process where the bearer of the role is added into another material entity (the target).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: drawing a conclusion based on data
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process in which data gathered in an investigation is evaluated in the context of existing knowledge with the objective to generate more general conclusions or to conclude that the data does not allow one to draw general conclusion

owl:Class.rdfs:label: planning
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a process of creating or modifying a plan specification

owl:Class.rdfs:label: mass analyzer
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A Mass analyzer is a device that separates ions according to their mass-to-charge ratio. All mass spectrometers are based on dynamics of charged particles in electric and magnetic fields in vacuum where the two laws of Lorentz force law and Newton's second law of motion apply.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ion source
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An ion source is a device that is part of a mass spectrometer that ionizes the material under analysis. The ions are then transported by magnetic or electric fields to the mass analyzer. Techniques for ionization have been key to determining what types of samples can be analyzed by mass spectrometry. Electron ionization and chemical ionization are used for gases and vapors. In chemical ionization sources, the material is ionized by chemical ion-molecule reactions during collisions in the source. Two techniques often used with liquid and solid biological samples include electrospray ionization (due to John Fenn PMID 2675315.) and matrix-assisted laser desorption/ionization (MALDI, due to M. Karas and F. Hillenkamp (Measuring Mass: From Positive Rays to Proteins by Michael A. Grayson (Editor) (ISBN 0-941901-31-9))).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ion detector
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An ion detector is a device that measures and records the charge induced or current produced when an ion passes by or hits a surface. Example: In a scanning instrument the signal produced in the detector during the course of the scan versus where the instrument is in the scan (at what m/Q) will produce a mass spectrum, a record of ions as a function of m/Q.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: contain function
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A contain function is a function to constrain a material entities location in space

owl:Class.rdfs:label: heat function
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A heat function is a function that increases the internal kinetic energy of a material

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material separation function
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material separation function is a function that increases the resolution between two or more material entities. The to distinction between the entities is usually based on some associated physical quality.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: filter function
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A filter function is a function to prevent the flow of certain entities based on a quality or qualities of the entity while allowing entities which have different qualities to pass through

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ionization function
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An ionization function is a function to physically convert an atom or molecule into an ion by adding or removing charged particles such as electrons or other ions.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cool function
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A cool function is a function to decrease the internal kinetic energy of a material below the initial kinetic energy of that type of material.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: environment control function
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An environmental control function is a function that regulates a contained environment within specified parameter ranges. For example the control of light exposure, humidity and temperature.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: measuring glucose concentration in blood serum assay
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: measuring glucose concentration in blood serum assay
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An assay that determines the concentration of glucose molecules in a blood serum sample

owl:Class.rdfs:label: extract
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an extract is a material entity which results from an extraction process

owl:Class.rdfs:label: adding material objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: is the specification of an objective to add a material into a target material. The adding is asymmetric in the sense that the target material largely retains its identity

owl:Class.rdfs:label: analyte measurement objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an assay objective to determine the presence or concentration of an analyte in the evaluant

owl:Class.rdfs:label: assay objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an objective specification to determine a specified type of information about an evaluated entity (the material entity bearing evaluant role)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: analyte assay
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An assay with the objective to capture information about the presence, concentration, or amount of an analyte in an evaluant.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: target of material addition role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role of a material entity that is realized in an "adding a material entity into a target" process where the bearer of the role (the target) receives the addition of another material entity.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: normalized data set
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A data set that is produced as the output of a normalization data transformation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: measure function
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Measure function is a function that is borne by a processed material and realized in a process in which information about some entity is expressed relative to some reference.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material transformation objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an objective specifiction that creates an specific output object from input materials.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: manufacturing
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process with the objective to produce a processed material which will have a function for future use.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: manufacturing objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: is the objective to manufacture a material of a certain function (device)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: study design execution
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a planned process that carries out a study design

owl:Class.rdfs:label: clinical chemistry assay
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An analyte assay which uses analytical methods to produce measurements and data on the concentration of chemical parameters (analytes) present in a bodily fluid collected from an organism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: manufacturer role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Manufacturer role is a role which inheres in a person or organization and which is realized by a manufacturing process.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: scattered molecular aggregate
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: Discussion in Karslruhe with, among others, Alan Rector, Stefan Schulz, Marijke Keet, Melanie Courtot, and Alan Ruttenberg. With inspiration from the paper Granularity, scale and collectivity: When size does and does not matter, Alan Recto, Jeremy Rogers, Thomas Bittner, Journal of Biomedical Informatics 39 (2006) 333-349
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a material entity that consists of all the molecules of a specific type that are located in some bounded region and which is part of a more massive material entity that has parts that are other such aggregates

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hematology assay
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An assay that studies phenotypes of an organism involving its blood and blood producing organs using a variety of techniques and instruments

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material separation objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: is an objective to transform a material entity into spatially separated components.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: urine specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a portion of urine collected from an organism

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material combination
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: is a material processing with the objective to combine two or more material entities as input into a single material entity as output.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: device setting
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a quality inheres_in some device and is concretization of some (device_setting_specification and is_about a quality of the device

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a material entity derived from a portion of blood collected from an organism

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen collection process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process with the objective to obtain a material entity for potential use as an input upon which measurements or observations are performed.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sample from organism
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a material obtained from an organism in order to be a representative of the whole

owl:Class.rdfs:label: portioning objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material separation objective aiming to separate material into multiple portions, each of which contains a similar composition of the input material.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: separation into different composition objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material separation objective aiming to separate a material entity that has parts of different types, and end with at least one output that is a material with parts of fewer types (modulo impurities).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen collection objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A objective specification that is fulfilled by obtaining a material entity for potential use as an input upon which measurements or observations are performed.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material combination objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: is an objective to obtain an output material that contains several input materials.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glucose tolerance test
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An assay that measures glucose clearance from blood over time by repeated glucose measurement in blood serum or plasma after the administration of a glucose bolus in-vivo. This assay can be used to evaluate the severity of insulin resistance or the efficiency of glucose clearance.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: host role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: host role is a role played by an organism and realized by providing nourishment, shelter or a means of reproduction to another organism within the organism playing the host role

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material sample role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material sample role is a specimen role borne by a material entity that is the output of a material sampling process.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material sample
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material entity that has the material sample role

owl:Class.rdfs:label: study design independent variable
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a directive information entity that is part of a study design. Independent variables are entities whose values are selected to determine its relationship to an observed phenomenon (the dependent variable). In such an experiment, an attempt is made to find evidence that the values of the independent variable determine the values of the dependent variable (that which is being measured). The independent variable can be changed as required, and its values do not represent a problem requiring explanation in an analysis, but are taken simply as given. The dependent variable on the other hand, usually cannot be directly controlled

owl:Class.rdfs:label: study design dependent variable
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: dependent variable specification is part of a study design. The dependent variable is the event studied and expected to change when the independent variable varies.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material maintenance objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An objective specification maintains some or all of the qualities of a material over time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: informed consent process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process with the objective to inform a person or their legal representative of legally and ethically relevant facts about a process that the person in question is asked to participate in, and which results in a documented decision as to whether the person in question will participate.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be treated with active ingredient role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: to be treated with active ingredient role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A study subject role which begins to exist when a subject is assigned to be one of those who will receive active ingredient, and is realized in a study execution in which they receive the active ingredient

owl:Class.rdfs:label: to be treated with placebo role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A study subject role which begins to exist when a subject is assigned to be one of those who will receive a placebo, and realized in a study execution in which they receive the placebo
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: to be treated with placebo role

owl:Class.rdfs:label: research organization
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organization formed with a goal to have its members conduct investigations

owl:Class.rdfs:label: measurement device
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A device in which a measure function inheres.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material maintenance
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process with the objective to maintain some or all of the characteristics of an input material over time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: study intervention
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process that is the part of the execution of an intervention design study which is varied between two or more subjects in the study.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material separation device
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A device with a separation function realized in a planed process

owl:Class.rdfs:label: service consumer role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a role which inheres in a person who uses a service

owl:Class.rdfs:label: service provider role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: is a role which inheres in a person or organization and is realized in in a planned process which provides access to training, materials or execution of protocols for an organization or person

owl:Class.rdfs:label: compound treatment design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an intervention design in which the treatment is the administration of a compound

owl:Class.rdfs:label: processed specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen that has been intentionally physically modified.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: container
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A device that can be used to restrict the location of material entities over time

owl:Class.rdfs:label: dose specification
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a directive information entity that describes the dose that will be administered to a target

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequence data
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A data item that representing the primary structure of a macromolecule(it's sequence) sometimes associated with an indicator of confidence of that measurement.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: dose
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A measurement datum that measures the quantity of something that may be administered to an organism or that an organism may be exposed to. Quantities of nutrients, drugs, vaccines and toxins are referred to as doses.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: administration of material to specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The directed combination of a material entity with a specimen.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: questionnaire
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A document with a set of printed or written questions with a choice of answers, devised for the purposes of a survey or statistical study.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleic acid extract
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An extract that is the output of an extraction process in which nucleic acid molecules are isolated from a specimen.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: environmental control device
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An environmental control device is a device which has the function to control some aspect of the environment such as temperature, or humidity.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: high performance liquid chromatography instrument
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A liquid chromatography instrument that consists of a reservoir of mobile phase, a pump, an injector, a separation column, and a detector. The pump (rather than gravity) provides the higher pressure required to propel the mobile phase and analyte through the densely packed column.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleic acid sequencer
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An device that is used to determine the order of nucleotides in nucleic acid sequences.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: protein sequencer
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An device that is used to determine the order of amino acids in protein sequences.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: liquid chromatography instrument
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A chromatography device that dissolves a mixture in liquid mobile phase to separate the analyte to be measured from other molecules in the mixture and allows it to be isolated

owl:Class.rdfs:label: service
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process in which a service provider performs a task (i.e. a planned process) for a service consumer.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: quality control testing design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A study design in which some aspects of the experiment is quality controlled for the purposes of quality assurance.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: dose response design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A study design that examines the relationship between the size of the administered dose and the extent of the response.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen from organism
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen that derives from an anatomical part or substance arising from an organism. Examples of tissue specimen include tissue, organ, physiological system, blood, or body location (arm).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material maintenance service
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material processing service in which a service provider makes physical modifications to a specified input material, such that at least one of the specified outputs of this process is a modified version of a specified input material.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material service
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A service which has a material entity as specified input and/or specified output.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material analysis service
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A service in which a service consumer provides some input material and a service provider performs some analysis of this material to generate data that is returned to the service consumer.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material storage service
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A storage service in which a service consumer provides some material as input which a service provider stores and returns as output.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: investigation description
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A textual entity that describes an investigation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen identifier
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A CRID symbol denotes a specimen and used to distinguish one specimen from another in an investigation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: PubMed ID
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A CRID symbol that is sufficient to look up a citation from the PubMed, a literature database of life sciences and biomedical information.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: investigation title
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A textual entity that denotes an investigation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Bioinformatics Resource Center
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organization that is one of the Internet-based research centers established and funded by NIAID (the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases). The Bioinformatics Resource Centers (BRCs) were formed in response to the threats posed by emerging and re-emerging pathogens, particularly CDC Category A, B, and C pathogens, and their potential use in bioterrorism. The intention of NIAID in funding these bioinformatics centers is to assist researchers involved in the experimental characterization of such pathogens and the formation of drugs, vaccines, or diagnostic tools to combat them.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: country name
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A textual entity that denotes a geographic location that is a site or part of a site that is identified as a country in the political geography.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: investigation identifier
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A CRID symbol used to identify an investigation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: grant identifier
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A CRID symbol used to identify a grant.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: analytical chromatography
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An analyte assay that uses a biomaterial's preferential affinity for either the mobile phase or the stationary phase to separate it from other materials and thereby detect its presence in an input material.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: grant
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A plan specification of organization A to give money to organization B so that B conducts investigations. Organization A has funder role and Organization B has research organization role.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: contact representative role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role inhering in a person who represents an institution, organization, or service provider and realized when communication is directed at them about the entity they represent.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: selection criterion
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A directive information entity which defines and states a principle of standard by which selection process may take place.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: OBI discussion summarized under the following tracker item : http://sourceforge.net/p/obi/obi-terms/678/

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen collector role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An Investigation agent role borne by a person or organization which is realized in a specimen collection process.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: drawing a conclusion
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process in which new information is inferred from existing information.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organization of specimen provider principal investigator
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organization that is the affiliation of the principal investigator providing the specimens for the investigation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: organization of specimen provider principal investigator

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organization of Bioinformatics Resource Center contact person
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organization that is the affiliation of the person who is contact representative of a Bioinformatics Resource Center
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: organization of Bioinformatics Resource Center contact person

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen-based scope of investigation specification
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A plan specification which specifies the scope of an investigation based on the heterogeneity of organisms or type of material that are the specified input of specimen collection.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen repository organization
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organization that provides a service to store and distribute specimens

owl:Class.rdfs:label: email address of Bioinformatics Resource Center contact person
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An email address of the person who is contact representative of a Bioinformatics Resource Center
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: email address of Bioinformatics Resource Center contact person

owl:Class.rdfs:label: email address of specimen collector
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An email address of the person collecting the specimen

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequencing facility organization
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organization that provides sequence determination service

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organization of specimen collector
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organization that is the affiliation of the person collecting the specimen

owl:Class.rdfs:label: email address of sequencing facility contact person
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An email address of the contact representative at the sequencing facility
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: email address of sequencing facility contact person

owl:Class.rdfs:label: investigation assay specification
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A plan specification which indicates the assay type used to obtain data.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organization of sequencing facility contact person
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organization that is the affiliation of the contact representative at the sequencing facility
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: organization of sequencing facility contact person

owl:Class.rdfs:label: comment on investigation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A textual entity that is about any of the aspects of an investigation worth noting

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen identifier assigned by specimen repository
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen identifier which is assigned by a specimen repository
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: specimen identifier assigned by specimen repository

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen identifier assigned by sequencing facility
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen identifier which is assigned by a sequencing facility
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: specimen identifier assigned by sequencing facility

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sample preparation for sequencing assay
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A sample preparation for assay that preparation of nucleic acids for a sequencing assay

owl:Class.rdfs:label: email address of specimen provider principal investigator
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An email address of the principal investigator providing the specimens for the investigation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: email address of specimen provider principal investigator

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequencing service
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A service provides sequencing service which is the realization of some sequencing such as RNA and DNA sequencing in which the service provider role is realized.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: testable hypothesis
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity that expresses an assertion that is intended to be tested.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: conclusion based on data
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity that is inferred from data.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cell freezing medium
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A processed material that serves as a liquid vehicle for freezing cells for long term quiescent stroage, which contains chemicls needed to sustain cell viability across freeze-thaw cycles.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: selection
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process with the objective to create a group of entities by applying a predefined criteria to a larger group of entities.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: scalar value specification
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A value specification that consists of two parts: a numeral and a unit label

owl:Class.rdfs:label: comparing prediction to measurement
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process in which predicted values for some thing are compared to measured values for that thing.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: value specification
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity that specifies a value within a classification scheme or on a quantitative scale.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: predicted value
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an information content entity that has been generated by a prediction process in which an estimate of a value of an entity is made which can be measured but without performing such a measurement. The value specification is intended to be close to the value a measurement process would produce modulo a prediction error.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: grant agency
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organization that provides funding support for projects such as investigations.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: collection of specimens
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material entity that has two or more specimens as its parts.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen set collection process
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen collection process that generates multiple specimens from one source (e.g. one organism) during a time period which for the purpose of the study can be considered to be taken at the same sampling time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimens collected in one encounter
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A collection of specimens that is collected from one source (e.g. one organism) during a time period which for the purpose of the study can be considered to be taken at the same sampling time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: human specimen set
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen set that is collected from one person during a time period which for the purpose of the study can be considered to be taken at the same sampling time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimens collected longitudinally
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A collection of specimens that was derived from the same source material entity at different time points in order to observe changes in that entity.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: container with environmental control
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A container with an environmental control function.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: digital object identifier
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A centrally registered identifier symbol used to uniquely identify objects given by International DOI Foundation. The DOI system is particularly used for electronic documents such as journal articles.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: high performance liquid chromotography assay
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An analytical chromatography assay that utilizes a high performance liquid chromatography instrument for separation of compounts in a solution.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecular analysis facility organization
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organization that provides molecular analysis service.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: measurand role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role borne by a material entity and realized in an assay which achieves the objective to measure the magnitude/concentration/amount of the measurand in the entity bearing evaluant role.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: bile specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen that is derived from bile.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: feces specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen that is derived from feces.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: digestive system fluid or secretion specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: digestive system fluid or secretion specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen that is derived from digestive system fluid or secretion.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: milk specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen that is derived from milk.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: saliva specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen that is derived from saliva.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sputum specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen that is derived from sputum.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sweat specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specimen that is derived from sweat.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood assay
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An assay that has a blood specimen as evaulant.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: reactant role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A role borne by a biological or chemical entity that participates or has molecular components that participate in a chemical reaction.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood plasma specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a material entity which corresponds to the liquid component of blood, in which the blood cells are suspended.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood serum specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material entity which derives from blood and corresponds to blood plasma without fibrinogen or the other clotting factors.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: specimen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material entity that is collected for potential use as an input upon which measurements or observations are performed.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cultured cell population
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A processed material comprised of a collection of cultured cells that has been continuously maintained together in culture and shares a common propagation history.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: glucose in solution
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A scattered aggregate of glucose molecules in a liquid

owl:Class.rdfs:label: data transformation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A completely executed planned process that produces output data from input data.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: data transformation objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An objective specification to transformation input data into output data

owl:Class.rdfs:label: data normalization objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A normalization objective is a data transformation objective where the aim is to remove systematic sources of variation to put the data on equal footing in order to create a common base for comparisons.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: normalization data transformation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A normalization data transformation is a data transformation that has objective normalization.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: scaling objective
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: is a data transformation objective where all, or some of a data set is adjusted by some data transformation according to some scale, for example a user defined minimum or maximum

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequential design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any design in which the decision as to whether to enroll the next patient, pair of patients, or block of patients is determined by whether the cumulative treatment difference for all previous patients is within specified limits. Enrollment is continued if the difference does not exceed the limits. It is terminated if it does

owl:Class.rdfs:label: observation design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: observation design is a study design in which subjects are monitored in the absence of any active intervention by experimentalists.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pool of specimens
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A pool of specimens is a mixture of a population of samples which have been gathered from one or more sample populations, obtained by the physical process of mixing individual specimens, e.g. mixing the DNA collected from the individual fish.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: validated information
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an information content entity which results from a validation process aimed at confirming a claim, a finding or a predicted information entity about a material entity or a process by experimental means.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: curated information
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An information content entity that has undergone a digital curation performed by a curator for accuracy checks and compliance with curation requirements. Information which has been assessed for accuracy by domain experts.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: randomized group participant role
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a role that borne by an organism and realized by some group randomization process

owl:Class.rdfs:label: extraction
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material separation in which a desired component of an input material is separated from the remainder

owl:Class.rdfs:label: filtration
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: OBI-Branch: adapted from wikipedia and wordnet
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: filtration is a process which separates components suspended in a fluid based on granularity properties relying on a filter device

owl:Class.rdfs:label: centrifugation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: centrifugation is a process separating molecules by size or density using centrifugal forces generated by a spinning rotor. G-forces of several hundred thousand times gravity are generated in ultracentrifugation

owl:Class.rdfs:label: storage
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process with the objective to preserve and protect material entities by placing them in an identified location which may have a controlled environment.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: group randomization
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A group assignment which relies on chance to assign materials to a group of materials in order to avoid bias in experimental set up.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: document editing
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: is a planned process with specified input original document and specified output edited document

owl:Class.rdfs:label: validation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a planned process with objective to check that the accuracy or the quality of a claim or prediction satisfies some criteria and which is assessed by comparing with independent results

owl:Class.rdfs:label: digital curation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Digital curation is the process of establishing and developing long term repositories of digital assets for current and future reference by researchers, scientists, and historians, and scholars generally.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: DNA sequencer
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A DNA sequencer is an instrument that determines the order of deoxynucleotides in deoxyribonucleic acid sequences.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: centrifuge
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A device with a rapidly rotating container that applies centrifugal force to its contents

owl:Class.rdfs:label: study design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A plan specification comprised of protocols (which may specify how and what kinds of data will be gathered) that are executed as part of an investigation and is realized during a study design execution.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: clinical study design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: Clinical Research Glossary Version 4.0 CDICS glossary group
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Plan for the precise procedure to be followed in a clinical trial, including planned and actual timing of events, choice of control group, method of allocating treatments, blinding methods; assigns a subject to pass through one or more epochs in the course of a trial. Specific design elements, e.g., crossover, parallel; dose-escalation [Modified from Pocock, Clinical Trials: A Practical Approach]

owl:Class.rdfs:label: repeated measure design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a study design which use the same individuals and exposure them to a set of conditions. The effect of order and practice can be confounding factor in such designs

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cross over design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a repeated measure design which ensures that experimental units receive, in sequence, the treatment (or the control), and then, after a specified time interval (aka *wash-out periods*), switch to the control (or treatment). In this design, subjects (patients in human context) serve as their own controls, and randomization may be used to determine the ordering which a subject receives the treatment and control

owl:Class.rdfs:label: n-to-1 design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: N-of-1 design is a cross-over design in which the same patient is repeatedly randomised to receive either the experimental treatment or its control (Senn, 1993).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: matched pairs design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A matched pair design is a study design which use groups of individuals associated (hence matched) to each other based on a set of criteria, one member going to one treatment, the other member receiving the other treatment.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: parallel group design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A parallel group design or independent measure design is a study design which uses unique experimental unit each experimental group, in other word no two individuals are shared between experimental groups, hence also known as parallel group design. Subjects of a treatment group receive a unique combination of independent variable values making up a treatment

owl:Class.rdfs:label: randomized complete block design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A randomized complete block design is_a study design which assigns randomly treatments to block. The number of units per block equals the number of treatment so each block receives each treatment exactly once (hence the qualifier 'complete'). The design was originally devised from field trials used in agronomy and agriculture. The analysis assumes that there is no interaction between block and treatment. The method was then used in other settings So The randomised complete block design is a design in which the subjects are matched according to a variable which the experimenter wishes to control. The subjects are put into groups (blocks) of the same size as the number of treatments. The members of each block are then randomly assigned to different treatment groups.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: balanced incomplete block design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: balanced incomplete block design is a kind of factorial design where all treatment pairs occur together within a block an equal number ?? times. ??ii' is the number of times treatment i occurs with i'

owl:Class.rdfs:label: loop design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A loop experiment design is where labeled extracts are compared in consecutive pairs. synonym: circular design

owl:Class.rdfs:label: reference design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A reference experiment design type is where all samples are compared to a common reference.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: latin square design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Latin square design is_a study design which allows in its simpler form controlling 2 levels of nuisance variables (also known as blocking variables).he 2 nuisance factors are divided into a tabular grid with the property that each row and each column receive each treatment exactly once.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: graeco latin square design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Greco-Latin square design is a study design which relates to Latin square design

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hyper graeco latin square design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: PRS to do

owl:Class.rdfs:label: factorial design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: factorial design is_a study design which is used to evaluate two or more factors simultaneously. The treatments are combinations of levels of the factors. The advantages of factorial designs over one-factor-at-a-time experiments is that they are more efficient and they allow interactions to be detected. In statistics, a factorial design experiment is an experiment whose design consists of two or more factors, each with discrete possible values or levels, and whose experimental units take on all possible combinations of these levels across all such factors. Such an experiment allows studying the effect of each factor on the response variable, as well as the effects of interactions between factors on the response variable.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: 2x2 factorial design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a factorial design which has 2 experimental factors (aka independent variables) and 2 factor levels per experimental factors

owl:Class.rdfs:label: fractional factorial design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A fractional factorial design is_a study design in which only an adequately chosen fraction of the treatment combinations required for the complete factorial experiment is selected to be run
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: http://www.itl.nist.gov/div898/handbook/pri/section3/pri334.htm From ASQC (1983) Glossary & Tables for Statistical Quality Control

owl:Class.rdfs:label: dye swap design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An experiment design type where the label orientations are reversed. exact synonym: flip dye, dye flip

owl:Class.rdfs:label: replicate design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A replicate experimental design type is where a series of replicates are performed to evaluate reproducibility or as a pilot study to determine the appropriate number of replicates for a subsequent experiments.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: self vs self design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A study design that investigates variance and error estimates in the experimental system, and is where the same extract is compared.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: time series design
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Groups of assays that are related as part of a time series.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: stopping rule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a stopping rule (criterion) is_a *rule* which causes a *stopping process* to happen

owl:Class.rdfs:label: compliance rule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a compliance rule is a rule which ensures a compliance process occurs

owl:Class.rdfs:label: standard compliance rule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a standard compliance rule is a compliance rule which defines conformity to a representation standard

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ethical standard compliance rule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an ethical standard compliance rule is_a *compliance rule* which enable a *ethical compliance process* to occur

owl:Class.rdfs:label: eligibility criterion
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: Adapted from Clinical Research Glossary Version 4.0 CDICS glossary group
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an eligibility criterion (rule) is_a selection criterion which defines and states the requirements (positive or negative) for an entity to be considered as suitable for a given task or participation in a process.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: inclusion criterion
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: Adapted from Clinical Research Glossary Version 4.0 CDICS glossary group
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an inclusion criterion (rule) is_a *eligibility criterion* which defines and states a condition which, if met, makes an entity suitable for a given task or participation in a given process. For instance, in a study protocol, inclusion criteria indicate the conditions that prospective subjects MUST meet to be eligible for participation in a study.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: exclusion criterion
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: Adapted from Clinical Research Glossary Version 4.0 CDICS glossary group
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an exclusion criterion (rule) is_a *eligibility criterion* which defines and states a condition which, if met, makes an entity unsuitable for a given task or participation in a given process. For instance, in a study protocol, exclusion criteria indicate the conditions that prospective subjects SHOULD NOT meet to be eligible for participation in a study

owl:Class.rdfs:label: human subject enrollment
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process with the objective to obtain a population of human subjects to participate in an investigation by determining eligibility of subjects and obtaining informed consent.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: collecting specimen from organism
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a process with the objective to obtain a material entity that was part of an organism for potential future use in an investigation

owl:Class.rdfs:label: administering substance in vivo
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A process by which a substance is intentionally given to an organism resulting in exposure of the organism to that substance.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material component separation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a material processing in which components of an input material become segregated in space

owl:Class.rdfs:label: group assignment
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: group assignment is a process which has an organism as specified input and during which a role is assigned

owl:Class.rdfs:label: maintaining cell culture
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A planned process with the objective to keep cells alive in a defined environment outside of an organism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: establishing cell culture
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a process through which a new type of cell culture or cell line is created, either through the isolation and culture of one or more cells from a fresh source, or the deliberate experimental modification of an existing cell culture (e.g passaging a primary culture to become a secondary culture or line, or the immortalization or stable genetic modification of an existing culture or line).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequencing assay
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An assay the uses chemical or biochemical means to infer the sequence of a biomaterial

owl:Class.rdfs:label: dialysis
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a protocol application that uses diffusion through a semi-permeable membrane to separate an input material into two fractions of different composition

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleic acid extraction
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a material separation to recover the nucleic acid fraction of an input material

owl:Class.rdfs:label: disposition to cause an allergic reaction
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000111: disposition to cause an allergic reaction
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The role borne by a material entity that is realized when it is recognized by the immune system and results in the occurrence of an allergic disease.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: allergic reaction
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: an allergic reaction is an pathologic immune response by an organism to a non-self entity that is normally harmless(the allergen)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: occurrence of allergy
