owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The process of an allergic disease occurring in an organism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: infectious disease
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: is a disease caused by an infectious agent

owl:Class.rdfs:label: allergy
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: is a disease in which an abnormally strong inflammatory immune response is triggered against non-self entities, and the immune response has no protective effect

owl:Class.rdfs:label: clinical history
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A series of statements representing health-relevant qualities of a patient and of a patient's family.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: laboratory finding

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phenotype
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A (combination of) quality(ies) of an organism determined by the interaction of its genetic make-up and environment that differentiates specific instances of a species from other instances of the same species.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: disease
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A disposition (i) to undergo pathological processes that (ii) exists in an organism because of one or more disorders in that organism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: clinical laboratory test
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A measurement assay that has as input a patient-derived specimen and as output a data item that is about a quality of the specimen.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: physical examination
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A sequence of acts of observing and measuring qualities of a patient performed by a clinician; measurements may occur with and without elicitation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: disease course
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The totality of all processes through which a given disease instance is realized.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: diagnosis
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The representation of a conclusion of a diagnostic process.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: treatment

owl:Class.rdfs:label: prognosis
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A hypothesis about some future part of a disease course.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: health care process

owl:Class.rdfs:label: health care process assay

owl:Class.rdfs:label: clinical data item

owl:Class.rdfs:label: altered population growth

owl:Class.rdfs:label: effect of non-nutrient environmental factors on population growth phenotype

owl:Class.rdfs:label: population growth in high osmolarity phenotype

Population growth may refer to growth rate, growth yield, or both.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: altered population growth in high osmolarity

owl:Class.rdfs:label: altered population growth range

owl:Class.rdfs:label: altered population phenotype

owl:Class.rdfs:label: altered population growth at high temperature

owl:Class.rdfs:label: solid configuration

owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased flexibility

owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased flexibility

owl:Class.rdfs:label: water composition

owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased water composition
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the reduction in amount of water the bearer contains.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pseudohermaphrodite
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of one sex and external sexual characteristics of the other sex.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: male pseudohermaphrodite
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of male and external sexual characteristics of female.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: female pseudohermaphrodite
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of female and external sexual characteristics of male.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: miscibility
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality of a liquid inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to mix with (dissolve in) another liquid.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phenotypic sex
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical expression of sexual characteristics.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: yellow green

owl:Class.rdfs:label: brown green
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A color consisting of brown and green hues.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: lilac

owl:Class.rdfs:label: yellow orange
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A color consisting of yellow and orange hue.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ochre
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A moderate yellow-orange to orange color.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: frozen
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being kept below its freezing point.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organismal quality
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased amount

owl:Class.rdfs:label: population quality
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality that inheres in an entire population or part of a population.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pale pink
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Pink color having high brightness and low saturation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: crystal configuration
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A solid configuration inhering in a material entity by virtue of its constituent atoms, molecules, or ions being arranged in an orderly repeating pattern extending in all three spatial dimensions.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: scirrhous
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A hardness quality of being rigid and resistant to pressure and fibrous.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: edibility
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being fit to be eaten.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: edible
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being suitable for use as food.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: inedible
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not being suitable for use as food.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecular quality
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity, a single molecule, atom, ion, radical etc.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: quality of a substance
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: neonatal
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A maturity quality inhering to a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being at the point or short after birth.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased quality
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased quality
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: decreased object quality
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: increased object quality
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: bronze
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A medium brown color with a metallic sheen, resembles the actual alloy bronze.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: intact female
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Female quality of having complete, unaltered reproductive organs

owl:Class.rdfs:label: intact male
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Male quality of having complete, unaltered reproductive organs.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: castrated male
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Male quality of being incapable to reproduce because of functional loss of the testicles from surgical removal or chemical means.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: beige
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A colour that is very pale yellowish brown.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: yellow brown
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A color consisting of yellow and brown hue.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: dark yellow brown
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A color consisting of yellow and brown hue and low brightness.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: light yellow brown
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A color consisting of yellow and brown hue and high brightness.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: firm
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A hardness quality of giving significant resistance to pressure.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: spayed female
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Female quality of being incapable to reproduce because of functional loss of the ovaries and/or uterus from surgical removal.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: male with DSD

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population who are otherwise male of a non-hermaphroditic species who has ambiguous or atypical congenital development of the reproductive system.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: diandrous
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A phenotypic sex quality inhering in a plant organism or a population of plants in which the flowers have two stamens.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: monandrous
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A phenotypic sex quality inhering in a plant organism or a population of plants in which the flowers have only one stamen.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: protogynous
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A sequential hermaphroditic quality whereby organisms start out as female and change to male at a later life stage.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: protandrous
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A sequential hermaphroditic quality whereby organisms start out as male and change to female at a later life stage.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: protogynous hermaphroditism
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A protogynous quality whereby organisms start out as female and change to hermaphrodite at a later life stage.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: protandrous hermaphroditism
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A protandrous quality whereby organisms start out as male and change to hermaphrodite at a later life stage.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: female with DSD
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population who are otherwise female of a non-hermaphroditic species who has ambiguous or atypical congenital development of the reproductive system.

female with disorder of sexual development

owl:Class.rdfs:label: normal object quality
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality of an object that has a value that is normal or average.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: normal flexibility
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A flexibility which is relatively normal or average.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: normal temperature
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A temperature which is relatively normal or average

owl:Class.rdfs:label: normal viscosity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A viscosity which is relatively normal or average

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sequential hermaphrodite
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A hermaphroditic quality that inheres in a population or organism where an organism changes is a different sexes during different life stages.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: quality of interaction of a substance with electromagnetic radiation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality of a substance on which or through which electromagnetic radiation impinges or traverses with respect to radiation. This substance quality changes the quality of the incident radiation with respect to any of: intensity, direction, scatter and wavelength.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: quantitative
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A quality of an entity that can be represented numerically, including anything that can be counted, measured, or given a numerical value.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: collection of organisms
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material entity that consists of two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: whole plant
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A plant structure (PO:0005679) which is a whole organism.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: plant structure
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A plant anatomical entity (PO:0025131) that is, or was, part of a plant, or was derived from a part of a plant.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: plant anatomical entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An anatomical entity that is or was part of a plant.
owl:Class.oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: 植物 解剖学（形態）的実体 (Japanese, exact)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: region
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A sequence_feature with an extent greater than zero. A nucleotide region is composed of bases and a polypeptide region is composed of amino acids.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: population stratification prior to sampling
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: PRS+AGB adapted from wikipedia: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stratified_sampling polled on June 7th,2013
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: stratification is a planned process which executes a stratification rule using as input a population and assign it member to mutually exclusive subpopulation based on the values defined by the stratification rule

owl:Class.rdfs:label: stratification rule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a stratification rule/criteria is a criteria used to determine population strata so that a stratification process implementing the rule can result in any member of the total population being assigned to one and only one stratum
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: adapted from wikipedia: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stratified_sampling polled on June 7th,2013

owl:Class.rdfs:label: stratum population
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a stratum population is a population resulting from a population stratification prior to sampling process which aims to produce homogenous subpopulations from an heterogeneous population by applying one or more stratification criteria

owl:Class.rdfs:label: statistical sampling
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: statistical sampling is a planned process which aims at assembling a population of observation units (samples) in as an unbiaised manner as possible in order to obtain or infer information about the actual population these samples have been drawn.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: simple random sampling
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Simple random sampling is a statistical sampling process which creates a sample of a size n entirely by chance. In such process, each unit has the same probability of being selected. Depending on the size of the population being sampled, the sampling process may be done with or without replacement

owl:Class.rdfs:label: anatomical structure
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material anatomical entity that is a single connected structure with inherent 3D shape generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organ
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Anatomical structure that performs a specific function or group of functions [WP].

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organ part
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A multicellular structure that is a part of an organ.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: intestine
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Segment of the alimentary canal extending from the stomach to the anus and, in humans and other mammals, consists of two segments, the small intestine and the large intestine.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: mouth
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The proximal portion of the digestive tract, containing the oral cavity and bounded by the oral opening. In vertebrates, this extends to the pharynx and includes gums, lips, tongue and parts of the palate. Typically also includes the teeth, except where these occur elsewhere (e.g. pharyngeal jaws) or protrude from the mouth (tusks).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: excreta
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A portion of organism substance that is the product of an excretion process that will be eliminated from the body. An excretion process is elimination by an organism of the waste products that arise as a result of metabolic activity.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: blood
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A fluid that is composed of blood plasma and erythrocytes.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: haemolymphatic fluid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Circulating fluid that is part of the hemolymphoid system. Blood, lymph, interstitial fluid or its analogs.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: secretion of exocrine gland
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A portion of organism substance that is produced by exocrine glands.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: organism substance
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material anatomical entity in a gaseous, liquid, semisolid or solid state; produced by anatomical structures or derived from inhaled and ingested substances that have been modified by anatomical structures as they pass through the body.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: material anatomical entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Anatomical entity that has mass.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: anatomical system
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Multicellular, connected anatomical structure that has multiple organs as parts and whose parts work together to achieve some shared function.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: multicellular organism
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Anatomical structure that is an individual member of a species and consists of more than one cell.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: anatomical cluster
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Anatomical group whose component anatomical structures lie in close proximity to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: tissue
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Multicellular anatomical structure that consists of many cells of one or a few types, arranged in an extracellular matrix such that their long-range organisation is at least partly a repetition of their short-range organisation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: stomach
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An expanded region of the vertebrate alimentary tract that serves as a food storage compartment and digestive organ. A stomach is lined, in whole or in part by a glandular epithelium.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: digestive system
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs devoted to the ingestion, digestion, and assimilation of food and the discharge of residual wastes.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: adipose tissue
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Portion of connective tissue composed of adipocytes enmeshed in areolar tissue.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: anatomical entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: urine
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Excretion that is the output of a kidney.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sweat
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Secretion produced by a sweat gland.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: colon
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A portion of the large intestine before it becomes the rectum. In mammals, the colon is the most part of the large intestine, excluding the vermiform appendix, the rectum and the anal canal.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: saliva
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A fluid produced in the oral cavity by salivary glands, typically used in predigestion, but also in other functions.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: milk
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An emulsion of fat globules within a fluid that is secreted by the mammary gland during lactation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: bile
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Vital aqueous secretion of the liver that is formed by hepatocytes and modified down stream by absorptive and secretory properties of the bile duct epithelium.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: feces
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Portion of semisolid bodily waste discharged through the anus[MW,modified].

owl:Class.rdfs:label: connective tissue
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Tissue with cells that deposit non-polarized extracellular matrix including connective tissue fibers and ground substance.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: female organism
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Gonochoristic organism that can produce female gametes.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: subdivision of digestive tract
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A proximal-distal subdivision of the digestive tract.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: alimentary part of gastrointestinal system
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The part of the digestive system that excludes the hepatobiliary system.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: bodily fluid
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Liquid components of living organisms. includes fluids that are excreted or secreted from the body as well as body water that normally is not.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: respiratory system fluid/secretion
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A portion of organism substance that secreted_by a respiratory system.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: mammary gland fluid/secretion
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A substance that is secreted by a mammary gland. The substance may differ depending on phase, with colostrum produced during pregancy/early lactation, and milk produced afterwards.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: adult organism
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A multicellular organism that existence_ends_with a post-juvenile adult stage and existence_starts_with a post-juvenile adult stage.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sputum
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Matter ejected from the lungs, bronchi, and trachea, through the mouth.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: multicellular anatomical structure
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An anatomical structure that has more than one cell as a part.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: food storage organ
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organ of the digestive tract that is capable of retaining and storing food.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: irregular connective tissue
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Connective tissue, which consists of a population of connective tissue cells, the intercellular matrix of which contains an irregular network of collagen and elastic fiber bundles. Examples: areolar tissue, mucoid tissue, connective tissue of peritoneum, connective tissue of fibrous pericardium.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: dense irregular connective tissue
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Irregular connective tissue is an irregular connective tissue, the intercellular matrix of which contains a dense irregular network of collagen and elastic fiber bundles. Examples: connective tissue of peritoneum, connective tissue of fibrous pericardium.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: dense connective tissue
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Dense connective tissue is mainly composed of collagen type I. Crowded between the collagen fibers are rows of fibroblasts, fiber-forming cells, that manufacture the fibers. Dense connective tissue forms strong, rope-like structures such as tendons and ligaments. Tendons attach skeletal muscles to bones; ligaments connect bones to bones at joints. Ligaments are more stretchy and contain more elastic fibers than tendons. Dense connective tissue also make up the lower layers of the skin (dermis), where it is arranged in sheets.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ingested food
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A substance that is consumed by the organism for food.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: digestive system element
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any of the organs or elements that are part of the digestive system. Examples: tongue, esophagus, spleen, crop, lunge feeding organ, tooth elements.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: disconnected anatomical group
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material anatomical entity consisting of multiple anatomical structures that are not connected to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit of measurement is a standardized quantity of a physical quality.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: length unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the distance between two points.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: mass unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of matter/energy of a physical object.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: time unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the dimension in which events occur in sequence.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: temperature unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the average kinetic energy of the particles in a sample of matter.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: substance unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which is a standardised quantity of an element or compound with uniform composition.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: kilogram
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A mass unit which is equal to the mass of the International Prototype Kilogram kept by the BIPM at Svres, France.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: gram
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a kilogram or 10^[-3] kg.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: minute
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A time unit which is equal to 60 seconds.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: hour
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A time unit which is equal to 3600 seconds or 60 minutes.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: day
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A time unit which is equal to 24 hours.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: week
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A time unit which is equal to 7 days.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: year
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A time unit which is equal to 12 months which in science is taken to be equal to 365.25 days.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which is one of a particular measure to which all measures of that type can be related.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: concentration unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which represents a standard measurement of how much of a given substance there is mixed with another substance.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: volume unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of space occupied by any substance, whether solid, liquid, or gas.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: frequency unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the number of repetitive actions in a particular time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pressure unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the force applied to a given area.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: volumetric flow rate unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of fluid which passes through a given surface per unit time .

owl:Class.rdfs:label: rate unit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A unit which represents a standard measurement occurrence of a process per unit time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: vaccine
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Material entity that is manufactured to realize the vaccine function.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: vaccination
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Process of administering a vaccine in vivo to a recipient (e.g., a human), with the intent to invoke a protective or therapeutic adaptive immune response.
